title: easy cheese chips
directions: Cut cheese and place 2 to 3-inches apart on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Drain on paper towel.

title: brown sugar-lemon chicken wings
directions: Prepare chicken.
Cut off tips of wings and excess skin and fat.
Split remaining joint so wing lies open.
Place in bowl with lemon juice to cover.
Marinate 6 hours at least (best overnight). Turn and stir occasionally.

title: cranberry concasse
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks in a large saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until the syrup is clear, about 3 minutes. Add the cranberries and cook for about 5 minutes or until the cranberries begin to pop.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a pie plate. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream of squash-corn soup
directions: Combine squash, corn and water.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Meanwhile, cook onion and green pepper in melted butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add to squash-corn mixture along with salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve in bowls.
Garnish with bacon, if you like.
Makes 9 cups.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread, and mix well.
Scoop out center of bread and save pieces.
Put dip in center of bread.
Use bread pieces to dip.
Continue pulling pieces from bread as needed.
Can serve with radishes and cauliflower around bread to serve more.

title: sweet peanut treat
directions: Bring sugar and water almost to a boil.
Add peanuts.
Stir and cook until all the water has evaporated.
Stir constantly. Spread on an oiled cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°, stirring once.
Cool.

title: oatmeal cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use teaspoon to drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add bread, sausage, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (325° if using glass dish). This is a good casserole for a brunch.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Place sugar, rhubarb and crushed pineapple and juice in a 3-quart cooking pan over medium heat.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring steadily.
Pour in strawberry jello. Bring to a rapid boil. Pour into clean jars.
Seal and wax.

title: russian tea
directions: Wrap cinnamon sticks and cloves in cheesecloth.
Add to tea and juices. Add enough sugar to sweeten.
Simmer 1 hour or more. Do not boil.
Take spices out.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin, oil, milk, strawberries, coconut and pecans.
Mix in four eggs, one at a time.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes (peeled or unpeeled) into skillet where you have melted 2 tablespoons fried meat grease.
Chop onion and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Cook with cover on until potatoes begin to brown.
Stir well.
When potatoes are almost done, sprinkle a small amount of water over potatoes; cover and continue cooking until done.
Season to taste.

title: chicken pilau
directions: Cook onions in 3 tablespoons butter until golden.
Add garlic, hot peppers, bay leaf, turmeric, coriander, cardamon, cloves and cinnamon sticks; cook briefly.
Add chicken and rice; cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Add the chicken broth, peas, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes.
Place on large platter.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked eggs.

title: cheese puffs(yields about 5 dozen)
directions: Melt cheeses and margarine together until mixture reaches fondue-like consistency.
Fold in egg whites.
Cool.
Cut bread in 3/4-inch cubes.
Coat each cube with cheese mixture by holding cube with fork and swirling on all sides, except bottom.
Place plain sides down on waxed paper covered sheets and freeze.
Transfer to bags for freezer storage.
When ready to bake, arrange bread cubes still frozen, on baking sheets and bake in a preheated 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and add hot cooked and drained broccoli.
Top with Ritz crackers (about 3/4 stack pack to make about 1/2-inch top).
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: blushing chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts. Put some olive oil on both sides of chicken and put in bread crumbs to coat.
Place heaps of cheeses, with a little sauce and sprinkle with oregano in the center of each breast.
Fold breast around filling and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with spaghetti sauce and coat chicken breasts with sauce. Top with mushrooms and more Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with pasta, rice or vegetables.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on High for 8 to 10 hours (overnight is great).
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
(Lots of gravy.)

title: mrs. barr's apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand.
In mixer bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix (or sift) flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture alternately with apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, oats and nuts, mixing well.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Sprinkle 2/3 cup coconut into bottom of crust.
Set aside. Spread remaining 2/3 cup coconut in even layer in a shallow pan. Toast at 350° for 7 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over pie. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put relish and 1/4 cup of vinegar through blender.
Add to sugar and rest of vinegar in large pot.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add Certo and return to boil.
Pour into hot clean jars and seal. (Food color enhances color.)
Serve with crackers and cream cheese.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain the artichoke hearts very well.
Cut them up into small pieces with a knife and place in a mixing bowl.
Add the mayonnaise and 2 teaspoons of the Parmesan cheese plus 4 tablespoons of the bread crumbs.
Mix well together.
Place this artichoke mixture into a medium size casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over artichoke mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve with crackers.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream oil, butter and both sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in and blend.

title: sour cream brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour and salt.
In small heavy pan bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil; take from heat and add immediately to dry ingredients.
Add sour cream, eggs and baking soda.
Mix well, batter will be thin, pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Ice while warm.

title: vegetable and fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; stir in other ingredients and refrigerate.
Very good.

title: yellow angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add water and beat until thickened.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly, about 10 minutes at high speed.
Fold in vanilla, orange and almond flavorings.
Fold flour and salt into egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until peaks are formed.
Fold into the batter and pour into ungreased 10-inch angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert pan and let cool 1 hour.
Frost with 7 Minute Frosting.

title: southern corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over moderately low heat.
Add onions and green peppers; cook 5 minutes until almost tender.
Blend in cornstarch.
Gradually add tomatoes, mixing well.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add sugar, salt and pepper.
Combine okra, corn and tomato mixture.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix 2 tablespoons melted margarine, bread crumbs and parsley.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cheese; add sugar and peanut butter.
Add Cool Whip. Save some for topping.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: frozen cookies
directions: Combine sugars and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add dates and nuts to sifted dry items.
Add to first mixture. Put in rolls or butter carton box and freeze.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: onion cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, a little at a time.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This can be frozen.

title: applesauce meatloaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except chili sauce.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread chili sauce over top of loaf; return to oven and bake another 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until lemon in color.
Add sugar, whipping cream, vanilla and almond flavoring, mixing well.
Pour into a one gallon container of the ice cream maker and add enough milk to the fill line or 1/2-inch from the top.

title: sweet and sour kielbasi
directions: Slice kielbasi into slices-thickness depends on your own preference.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, vanilla
and
melted
butter;
mix	well.
Add enough water to cornstarch	to
make it a little runny.
Blend cornstarch into egg mixture.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon into unbaked pie
shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick or knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 1 hour. Reheat and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marinated olives
directions: Place
olives
in
glass
container
with lid.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over olives.
Cap jar and shake to coat olives well.
Marinate at room temperature for 2 days, shaking
jar
daily.
Drain before serving.
Makes about 1 cup of olives.

title: oatmeal caramelites
directions: Melt the caramels and evaporated milk in double boiler; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, soda, salt and melted margarine.
Spread 1/2 of this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Spread caramel over oatmeal mixture.
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and pecans.
Put rest of the dry ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Cut while lukewarm.)

title: winter cabbage soup
directions: Cook bacon.
Add diced potatoes & rest of ingredients except half and half.
Bring soup to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered until vegetables are tender 30 - 40 minutes. Add half and half after vegetables are tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain and add next 7 ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain.

In greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread just enough sauce mixture to prevent sticking. Starting with noodles, layer noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1/3 sauce mixture. Repeat 2 times.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and add to beef.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 45 more minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: sesame ginger chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips and cover with water to make stock.
Add chicken broth to make 4 cups.
Split wings.
Heat stock and all other ingredients.
Thoroughly marinate wings in broth 36 to 48 hours, turning every 12 hours.
Line roasting pan with foil, place wings on foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and water.
Sift flour and salt, then add to mixture and stir.
Add pecans and mix.
Sprinkle with sugars and decorations.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes. Let cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar 2 times.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Shape into balls (1 1/2-inch).
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove pan from oven.
Push Kiss into cookie.
Bake an additional 2 to 5 minutes.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place rhubarb, strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Place in oven at 450°.
Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add oil and milk; stir to form a ball.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Put dot of butter on each spoonful.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle on biscuits.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix all ingredients until crumbly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Work from the center and have crust a little higher around edges.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, water and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except cinnamon dots.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Combine with onion, margarine, eggs, sage, paprika, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Stir in half the cheese.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and additional paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Add cream cheese and powdered sugar to Cool Whip.
Prepare pie crust with nuts pressed in bottom.
Bake pie shell to light brown. Add cheese mixture; top with fresh blueberries.
Chill.

title: cheese dip(crock-pot)
directions: Combine all in a crock-pot and melt.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and egg in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Reduce speed to low; add flour, orange juice, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until well mixed.
Divide dough into thirds; wrap in plastic food wrap.
Refrigerate until firm (2 to 3 hours).

title: spiced orange pot roast
directions: Brown meat slowly on both sides in shortening.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce, orange sections, sugar and grated orange rind over meat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and spices.
Cover and cook slowly until meat is very tender, about 2 hours longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: truffles
directions: Melt 8 ounces chocolate, cream and butter over low heat until smooth.
Cover and freeze 20 minutes.
Drop onto wax paper covered cookie sheet by 1 teaspoon scoops. Freeze 15 minutes. Quickly and gently roll into balls.
Freeze again 15 minutes until hard.

title: fabulous friday trail mix
directions: Each student brings and item and combines it with the other students' items in a large bowl.
The trail mix is to be eaten as the students do research for the upcoming unit.
This reward works best if used only once per unit of study.

title: egg in a frame
directions: With a glass or a biscuit cutter, cut out a circle from the middle of a piece of bread.
Eat the bread circle while you wait for the butter to melt in a skillet.
Place bread frame into skillet.
Break open egg into the hole in the bread.
Fry egg until done, turning over once with a spatula.

title: florence's standing rib roast
directions: Have butcher crack ribs and tie roast to bake.
Pour a layer of rock salt in bottom of Dutch oven.
Place roast (bone down) on this layer.
Pour remaining salt around sides and over top of meat to cover completely.
Bake in 325° oven until done to your test.

title: maple cream church spread
directions: After yogurt has been refrigerated overnight, put colander in 6-quart kettle with cheesecloth.
Pour in yogurt.
Put lid on and return to icebox.
Drain until thick like cream cheese.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger.
Mix everything together.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chocolate muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease 10 muffin cups.
Combine flour, sugar, and cocoa.
Stir to mix.
In another bowl, combine egg, chocolate milk, oil and extract. Whisk until well mixed. Combine two mixtures and stir just until mixed.
Batter should appear lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of muffin. Good served warm, plain or buttered. Honey butter is good with these muffins.

title: sausage rolls
directions: In bowl mix pastry mix.
Roll out on floured board.
Open package of sausage mix; cut in half.
Roll out length of pastry. To form pasties or apple puffs, cut in size of 3 inches.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Layer Crescent rolls in a pan.
Spread sausage over rolls. Pour beaten eggs over sausage.
Spread cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust with flour a 10-inch tube pan.

Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt into a large bowl. Cream the butter until fluffy and gradually beat in sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Alternately beat in flour mix (in fourths) and milk (in thirds), beginning with flour.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes inverted on rack. Cool completely before decorating cake with powdered sugar. Garnish with berries and mint, if desired.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cut Velveeta into cubes.
Melt on medium heat with milk.
Add soup and sauce.
Cook on low until hot.
Serve with chips.

title: turnips and beef
directions: Peel turnips and cut in quarters.
Put in pot with hamburg and cook until turnips are soft.

title: fresh apple cinnamon cake
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add apples, sugar and egg and mix with spoon.
Sift dry ingredients and mix until blended. Pour into a pan with a hole in the center (greased).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown ground beef; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, basil and oregano.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: snowblower(punch)
directions: In large saucepan, mix together cranapple juice, spices, rum and lemon slices.
Heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in mugs with lemon slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rapid boil. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour in greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Arrange chicken in sprayed baking dish. Drizzle butter over chicken. Place cooked and drained broccoli around chicken. Blend soup with cheese and milk; pour over chicken and broccoli. Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dr. lathrop's red flannel hash
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Saute onion in a large skillet at medium setting on burner.
Add diced potatoes, corned beef, beets and slightly beaten eggs (include juice from beets).
Gently turn until corned beef begins to brown.
Serve under eggs, sunny side up.
Season to taste.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough; otherwise, just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt; spray with Pam and sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside. Check with a fork.

title: miss mamie's corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: "charley's omelette"
directions: Combine first three items in a small bowl.
In an omelette pan, heat butter until foaming.
Add beaten eggs.
Cook as for a regular omelette.

title: chewy oatmeal toffee cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar, butter and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla, flour, baking soda, salt and rolled oats. Then stir in pecans and Heath bars.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop cookies.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: One hour before serving, fry bacon.
In bacon grease, cook rice, onion and pepper until rice is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, bay leaf, salt and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in ham, shrimp and pepper sauce. Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, until rice is tender; stir often.
Sprinkle with bacon when serving.
Extra chicken broth or tomato juice can be added if mixture is too dry.

title: cream cheese monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in half and flatten on lightly floured surface.
Place cream cheese cube on each.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Fold biscuit to enclose filling, sealing edges.
Heat margarine, brown sugar and syrup in saucepan until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Layer brown sugar mixture and biscuits alternately in greased Bundt pan until all ingredients are used. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan for 3 minutes before inverting onto serving platter.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream ingredients together and form a ball.
Roll in pecans. Chill for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and dice apples (to make about 4 cups).
In a large bowl, sprinkle cut-up apples with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add celery, grapes, walnuts and raisins.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together ingredients and press into 9 x 13 pan.

title: white cake icing
directions: Combine 1 cup 10x sugar and 1 egg white in a small mixing bowl.
Combine the remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Beat the first mixture until blended.
Beat the second mixture, then add first to second.
Beat well.
Frosts a 13 x 9-inch or a layer cake.

title: chicken cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken with sour cream, soup, cheeses, chilies and onion.
Mix well.
Fry tortillas one at a time in oil, about 5 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Place 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese and bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: very easy and impressive baked alaska
directions: Pack ice cream into the shell.
Place in freezer.

title: boudin balls
directions: Boil the pork roast in seasoning and water until meat falls off the bone.
Saute the bell pepper and green onions in butter until tender.
Chop the meat and add all ingredients
together. Form into meatballs, roll in flour and deep fat fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve as appetizer.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook all ingredients, but cornstarch and water, in a pan until apples are tender, but not soft.
Mix the cornstarch and water together and add to mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into large bowl. Cut in butter.
Beat egg with 2 tablespoons water and extract. Add to flour.
Knead dough on floured surface.
Refrigerate 1 hour in waxed paper.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets, boil until done.
Peel and slice.
Put in all ingredients and boil beets until hot.
Put in jars and seal. Makes 3 or 4 pints.

title: delicious orange rolls
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Crumble yeast in water.
Add the juice, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and well beaten egg.
Then, add flour all at once and mix thoroughly.
Add softened Crisco and mix well. Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out as for biscuits.
Spread with oleo or butter, 4 tablespoons sugar and orange rind.
Roll up as for cinnamon rolls and cut into small rolls about 1-inch thick.
Let rise until double and bake in hot oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until rolls are a delicate brown and spring back when tested.

title: no sugar bars
directions: Cook fruits in water for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into loaf cake pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Excellent for diabetics.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out pulp leaving 1/4-inch wall.
Place cut side down.
Cover loosely, microwave until crisp-tender 5 to 6 minutes.
Cover and microwave reserved pulp, onions and margarine in 1 1/2-quart bowl until tender, 6 to 7 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese, tomato, salt and pepper. Turn zucchini shells cut side up.
Spoon mixture into shells. Cover loosely, microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: posole
directions: Boil
corn
for six to seven hours.
Add chunks of pork or beef,
chile
pods,
garlic and salt.
Cook until meat and corn are tender.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Makes about 100 cookies.
Good for church suppers.
Recipe can be halved.

title: cornbread(lower-cal)
directions: Put oil in 9-inch pan (iron skillet is best).
Heat hot enough to sizzle.
Mix all other ingredients well, pour in skillet.

title: teriyaki roll-ups
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, onion, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, ginger and salt in a medium bowl.
Add meat and stir to coat strips evenly with sauce.
Marinate 30 minutes at room temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: fettuccine and goat cheese
directions: Cook fettucine al dente.
Meanwhile, heat oil and garlic over moderately low heat just until mixture is hot.
Drain fettucine well and toss with oil mixture, parsley, mint, tomatoes and goat cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: spaghetti
directions: Noodles:
First you get a big pot and put it on the stove. Put water in it and boil the water. When the water is boiled, you put the noodles in. Stir every few minutes until it is done.
Pour out water.

title: kehl's favorite tacos
directions: This recipe depends on how large your family is, so adjust accordingly.
This is large enough for 6 to 8 people.

title: dorothy lynch salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart jar and shake.
Start with 1/2 cup vinegar and add to taste.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: fried pumpkin blossoms
directions: Remove center stem of blossoms.
Wash blossoms gently in large basin of salted water.
Pat dry on paper towel.
Beat together egg, water, salt and pepper.
Combine breadcrumbs and cheese.
Dip blossoms into egg mixture, then into breadcrumb mixture.
Saute in hot oil until golden, turning once.
Serve as an hors d'oeurve or with salad as a light lunch.

title: spanish hash
directions: Chop peppers and onions and saute in a little oil.
Add sausage and hamburger meat; mix well and cook until brown.
Add tomato paste and spaghetti and cook for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(I also add some garlic salt.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Press into spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Toss all together.
Cover with tight lid and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: rice and link sausages
directions: Saute ham; add tomato, onion, pepper and sausages.
Mix well; add rice and cook for 2 minutes.
Add achote coloring, salt and water; mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook over medium heat until rice is tender.
Cooking time approximately 25 minutes.

title: angel cake dessert
directions: Break cake in pieces.
Put in 9 x 13 inch dish.
Mix pudding with one cup milk.
Mix with ice cream.
Pour on cake.
Make jello, jell slightly.
Put orange slices in jello.
Pour over cake.
Chill and serve.

title: russian drop cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, raisins, coconut, nuts, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all real well.
Drop by tsp. on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° oven until light brown.
These get better with age.
Keep in airtight tins.

title: ice cream
directions: Put the milk or cream on to boil.
If cream is used, six eggs will be sufficient; if milk, use eight.
Beat the yolks of the eggs and the sugar very light,
and then beat the whites to a stiff froth.
Take the milk off the fire and pour it over the sugar and yolks, stirring all the while.
Then add the whites, mixing thoroughly, and two tablespoonfuls of extract of either lemon or vanilla.
Set to cool and then turn into the freezer, pack and stir around in the ice for about ten minutes, and finish as in making and freezing ice cream.
This ice cream is the basis of all ice cream.

title: blackberry roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixer bowl, combine first 4 ingredients until butter is worked into fine crumbs.
Blend in the cheese and then the milk; do not overmix.
Roll the dough out into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle about 1/3 inch thick.
Sprinkle blackberries on top, then add 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Start from long end and roll like a jelly roll. Place on greased baking pan with seam down.
Pinch ends together and sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with cream.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender. Fry the bacon until crisp- remove from the skillet and saute the onions in the bacon dripping.
Mix all of the other ingredients together in a pan and heat thoroughly.
Add the potatoes, onions and bacon. Serve hot.

title: frank potato chowder
directions: In saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Add 1 cup of water; bring to boil.
Cover and boil gently for 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add frank slices.
Blend flour, pepper and milk. Stir into vegetables;
bring to boiling.
Cook for 2 minutes more.
Add margarine and serve with paprika and other pat of margarine.
Serves 6.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Chop onion, peppers and cabbage. Add to beef in large soup pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in buttermilk, brown sugar and shortening. Mix in the remaining ingredients until flour is moistened. Batter may be lumpy.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla; fold into Cool Whip.
Pour and spread into crusts. Refrigerate.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all together and store in large plastic canister.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the onion and cook
until
tender, stirring occasionally.
Add the bread cubes and continue
cooking
until some of the cubes are toasted, stirring
occasionally.
Remove
from
the
heat. Combine the cubes
with
all the other ingredients, except the cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of
the mixture into a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with
of
the grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain grease. Brown green pepper, celery, mushrooms and season with salt and pepper.
Mix in large pot, tomato soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add drained, browned beef and vegetable mixture.
Heat until hot and well mixed.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bake
cake as directed on box; while cake is baking, put Eagle Brand,
semi-sweet
chocolate and 1/2 cup milk together. Add nuts
or
coconut,
poke holes in cooked cake.
Pour Eagle Brand mixture over cake.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Put dissolved yeast into buttermilk.
Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together.
Add buttermilk and shortening; mix together and beat well.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut place in baking pan.
Let raise to desired thickness.
Bake at 425° for approximately 20 minutes or less (to desired brownness).

title: 24 hour salad
directions: *Bananas and apple can be added, but not until just before serving to keep from turning dark in color.

title: quick honey white bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, put 2 cups flour, dry milk, yeast and salt.
Pour in water; beat 1 minute.
Add butter and honey; beat another minute.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto floured board; knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in bowl; let rise (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; knead gently.
Shape into loaves (3 to 4, depending on size).
Let rise (1/2 hour). Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Great texture!

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend all of the ingredients; mix well.
Serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend flour, oleo and pecans and pat mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
When mixed well, fold in half of large carton Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix instant puddings, adding 3 cups milk and mix well.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remainder Cool Whip.
You can garnish with grated chocolate.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: canned peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Pack into quart jars.
Add sugar and very little water.
Cook on low heat; let come to boil.
Boil on low for 1 1/2 hours, then bring to a hard boil.
Add box of Sure-Jell; cook until syrup thickens.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder and pepper.
Cut in butter and stir in grated cheese.
Add milk and mix quickly for dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead for 30 seconds.
Roll out and cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Space evenly.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Serves 12 to 15.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).
In 13 x 9 baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients and press down firmly with fork. Bake 25 minutes; cool.
Store covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 bars.

title: baked apples
directions: Spread cranberry sauce over apples.
Mix melted margarine with rolled oats and brown sugar; spread over cranberry sauce.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked brie with pecans(french)
directions: Place Brie in an ovenproof dish.
Toast pecans in butter and stir in parsley.
Heat cheese at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes or until just warm.
Top with pecan mixture.
Serve immediately with unsalted crackers or sliced French bread.

title: apple pie filling spice cake
directions: Mix spice cake mix, oil and eggs with electric mixer until blended. Add apple pie filling and mix with electric mixer just until blended, so it breaks up apples some.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This is a dense, moist cake.

title: raisin cake
directions: Stew
for
5 minutes raisins, water, sugar and shortening. Cool,
then
add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg pie
directions: Whip eggs in mixer thoroughly; add sugar gradually and then add milk.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake for 10 minutes.
Then turn oven to 275° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: "pete's" cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast in a large bowl.
Heat milk, water and 1/2 cup margarine to lukewarm or microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of flour and eggs; beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make batter like biscuit batter. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 2 hours or up to 2 days.
Turn onto floured board.
Roll out; brush with melted butter.

title: easy "hot water" pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add hot water and butter to mixture.
Knead until smooth.
May add extra flour if too sticky.
Roll on with rolling pin on floured surface.
Place in 10-inch pie pan.
Bake with favorite filling.
Cover edges of crust with foil until the last 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat through.
Spread on chicken.

title: chess cake
directions: Blend
cake mix, butter and 1 egg together and press in oblong 9	x
13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese and
pour over
other
mixture.
Bake
at
for 45 to 50 minutes.
This can
also be made using lemon cake mix instead of yellow cake mix.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in electric skillet to 325°.
Add meat and brown. Remove to serving dish.
Add onions and pepper slices.
Cook until tender.
Remove and put with steak.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and soy sauce.
Add garlic, salt and pepper and put in skillet. Then put in meat, onion and peppers.
Cook until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken breasts in baking pan.
Whip soup, then spread soup over chicken.
Layer with cheese over soup.
Melt butter; mix with 2/3 cup stuffing.
Sprinkle stuffing over cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of pan.

title: funnel cake
directions: In skillet, put 1/2 cup oil.
Cook and dust with powdered sugar.

title: yummy pasta salad
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add rotini pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain. In a skillet over medium heat, place the cubed chicken and dab with ranch dressing.
Pour enough Italian dressing into the skillet to cover the bottom of the pan.
Cook the chicken until it is nice and brown.
Mix together pasta, chicken, black olives and Italian dressing (to taste).
Serve hot or cold.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomatoes and chilies, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Combine thoroughly; simmer 15 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13 baking dish and place 6 tortillas in pan, overlapping if need be. Top each tortilla with 1/2 of meat mixture and 1/2 of cheese. Repeat with tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly hot and cheese is melted. Good served with a dollop of sour cream.
Fresh tomatoes or frozen may be used.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Doritos and cheese together.
Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with crushed Doritos.
Pour mixture over that and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish pork chops with rice
directions: Wash rice thoroughly and boil in salted water for about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Brown pork chops in frying pan, then remove. Add the onion and celery to drippings and brown.
Return the chops to the pan on top of the onion.
Put a mound of rice on top of each chop.
Pour the tomato juice around the chops and on top. Scatter parsley over all and bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for one hour.
Yields 6 servings, 1 chop each.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and shape into a ball.

title: mimi's sour pickles
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in 1 gallon container and add small pickling cucumbers.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Halve zucchini and hull insides.
Combine onion, beef, rice to fill and tomato sauce.
Cook bacon.
Fill boats with mixture. Place in baking dish.
Add more tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Take out.
Place cheese and bacon atop.
Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: berry patch crisp
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine.
Add oats. Mix about 1/4 of crumb mixture with blueberries and spread into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute butter, basil or fresh basil, mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Mix together mushroom soup, milk, egg and pimento.
Add to this mixture chicken, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Line a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with cooked lasagna noodles, then a layer of chicken-cheese mixture, noodles, cheese, etc., until mixture is gone.
Make a basic white sauce with lots of garlic for the top layer of noodles and sprinkle generously with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spinach and mandarin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dressing.
Add dressing; toss gently.
Serve.

title: gobble goodies
directions: Melt the oleo and marshmallows together.
Remove from heat and add the cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Cool 10 minutes.
Butter hands and shape cereal mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Twist apart sandwich cookies.
Frost inside of cookie half.
Press 3 candy corns into the frosting in the shape of a fan.
Press a cereal ball into the center of each cookie.
Put more frosting on other cookie half and stick them to the bottoms of cereal balls.
Put a dab of frosting on a candy corn and stick it onto cereal ball to make the turkey's head.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears using coarse blade and drain off excess juice. Grind peppers and onions.
Combine all ingredients, bring to boil and boil 20 minutes or until done.
Pack into standard canning jars and seal.
Process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend until creamy in blender.
Toss with fresh spinach, hard boiled eggs, cooked crumbled bacon and mushrooms.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix and press cake mix, oleo and egg in oblong pan.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Melt over low heat the peanut butter chips, corn syrup, vanilla and oleo.
Add Rice Krispies and 2 cups dry roasted peanuts.
When cake is done, pour miniature marshmallows on top, then pour melted peanut butter mixture on top of marshmallows.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir into buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Cover and chill.
When ready to use, roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut off biscuits with 2-inch cutter and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Dough will keep several weeks in the refrigerator. You can add more flour and water to weaken mixture (of too strong a yeast taste).
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen (2-inch) biscuits.

title: crab cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in dish.
Bake uncovered until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Garnish with zucchini slices if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter.

title: cold stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix well with the other ingredients. Stuff mushroom caps.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, corn syrup, eggs and evaporated milk.
Stir butter into the hot milk.
Combine brown sugar, salt and spices. Mix until well blended.
Combine all three mixtures.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Stem and clean caps gently.
Mix softened cream cheese with garlic powder and bacon bits.
Brown in oven at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Mix up and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together, put into a bake dish.
Add enough Milk to make real thin.

title: banana mallow dessert
directions: Place banana slices and marshmallows in a serving bowl; set aside. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
If necessary, remove unmelted ice.
Pour over banana and marshmallows in bowl or individual dessert dishes. Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in order listed: pineapple, pie filling, cake mix, pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic cheese dunk
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sour cream.
Add dressing mix and Tabasco and beat until smooth.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix to dissolve jello in water. Add the sugar and strawberries.
Let start to thicken, then fold in Cool Whip. Break 1/2 loaf into pieces.
Put
in layer pan and cover with half the mixture.
Finish breaking cake and cover with rest of the mixture.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill and serve.

title: grandma's banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350°, one large loaf pan, 45 to 50 minutes (approximately) or 2 round layers, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Moisten with 1/2 mayonnaise and 1/2 homemade dressing.
Chill. Before serving, add 1 large can of shoestring potatoes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend together in blender.
Refrigerate and serve with vegetable of your choice.

title: hunters special
directions: Put layer of beans in skillet on low heat, then layer of potatoes, layer of bologna.
Repeat until all bacon and bologna are gone, then add salt and pepper. Cook until done and serve with beans.

title: mrs. field's snowy white chocolate crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl combine flour and cocoa. Mix well with wire whisk and set aside.
In medium bowl cream butter and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed.
Add vanilla and egg, beat until light and smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl. Add flour and cocoa mixture.
Blend on low speed until fully incorporated.
(Dough will be dry and crumbly.)
Shape a level tablespoonful of dough into a 3 1/2-inch log.
Slightly bend log to form crescent shape.
Place crescents 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until outside is hard and inside is soft.
Cool on pan for 2 to 3 minutes, then transfer to flat surface.
While still warm, roll cookies in confectioners sugar until cooled.

title: best "key lime" pie
directions: Gently mix limeade, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell of your choice.

title: soft maple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 9 minutes.
Cool.
Frost if desired.

title: alan's vegetable pizza toppings
directions: Spread a thin coating of pizza sauce on the two shells. Arrange vegetables, sprinkle generously with fresh Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake in 400° oven 25 minutes or until done.

title: stir-fried green beans with walnuts
directions: In a wok, heat the oil over high heat to 375° and in it fry the walnuts for 10 to 20 seconds or until they are golden. Transfer the walnuts with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain and chop them coarse.

Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the oil; heat the remaining oil over high heat until it is hot, but not smoking, and in it stir-fry the beans and the red pepper flakes for 1 minute or until the beans are coated with the oil.
Add 1/3 cup water and steam the beans, covered, over moderate heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until they are just tender, but still crisp.
Add the walnuts and the soy sauce mixture and stir-fry the mixture over high heat for 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until the beans and walnuts are coated well with the sauce.
Season the mixture with salt and pepper and transfer it with a slotted spoon to a heated serving dish.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts and pour into greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, veggies, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of French onions. Place in 8 x 12 baking pan. Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Uncover. Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles. Cut into strips. Place on top crisscross of mixture. Bake 15 minutes. Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: frog's eye salad
directions: Cook macaroni 7 to 9 minutes.
Strain fruit from juices and refrigerate fruit; retain juices.
In saucepan, cook retained juices with sugar, eggs, flour and salt.
Bring to a boil and continue cooking about 7 minutes until thickened, stirring often with a wire whisk.
Pour this sauce over macaroni.
Mix and let set on counter for 1 1/2 hours.
Then refrigerate until cold.
Mix in fruit and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 5 hours.
Serve and enjoy!

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, green pepper, salt, pepper and then add 1/2 can beef bouillon. Combine A.1. sauce, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, brown sugar and cooked spaghetti. Mix well all the ingredients and put in baking dish. Top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn-squash bake
directions: Cut the unpeeled squash into 1-inch rounds (zucchini is a summer squash).
Cook the cut squash in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash with a fork.
Saute the chopped onion in 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Combine the mashed squash, sauteed onion ,corn, Swiss cheese and eggs.
Turn into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine the Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and other tablespoon of margarine, which has been melted. Sprinkle the topping on the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving to allow casserole to set.
Serves 6.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart glass microwave container (bread size) for 6 minutes, turning every 2 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour.
When mixed well, add water, bouillon cubes, cumin and chili powder.
Bring to a boil. When bouillon is dissolved, put tortillas in sauce until soft. Add cheese and hamburger meat to edge of tortilla.
Roll tightly. Repeat until pan is full.
Pour remaining hamburger meat into sauce and pour over enchiladas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Very moist!

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in margarine and drain.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: garden salad pizza
directions: Put a pizza stone on the lowest rack of the oven.
Preheat to 400°.
(If you use a metal pan instead, do not preheat the pan.) Toss the vegetables with oil and vinegar.
Let set for 30 minutes. Cover two (12-inch) pizza shells such as Boboli, with the cheese (leaving a 1/4-inch rim); sprinkle the vegetable mixture over the cheese.
Slide the pizzas onto the pizza stone.
Bake for 15 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Work in the shortening and cut in the sweet potatoes.
Moisten with milk using only enough to form a soft, tender dough.
Turn onto a slightly floured board. Knead until just smooth and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch biscuits.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) until browned.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Mix together first three ingredients, then refrigerate until partly set.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix in drained oranges.
Refrigerate until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Add to above mixture.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° 1 hour until done (toothpick comes out dry).

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and boil in salt water until tender.
Mix tuna fish, egg, cracker crumbs, peppers and onions.
Stuff peppers.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over peppers and pat with margarine.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar, pecans and butter.
Pat into bottom of oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together well cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Put on top of pretzel mixture and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until Jell-O begins to thicken.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi italiano
directions: In large shallow broiler-proof pan, pour dressing over shrimp. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, at least 2 hours.
Broil shrimp with dressing, turning shrimp and basting with dressing until done.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Add chives.
Put into large casserole bowl (ovenproof).
Put pats of butter on top of potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients and roll into small round balls.
You can fry or bake.

title: country club squash
directions: Wash squash; trim off ends.
Cook squash and onions in boiling salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Combine squash, sour cream, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: grilled cheese and tomato soup for hungry dads who work overtime
directions: Butter the bread on both sides.
Add 2 slices cheese for sandwich.
Grill in a buttered frying pan until golden brown. While this is cooking, add 1 can of milk to tomato soup.
Heat until it boils.
Serve with a smile.

title: ebleskiver(pancake balls)
directions: Separate the eggs and beat the whites stiff; mix other items together until smooth and allow batter to set 30 minutes to let baking powder work.
Fold in egg whites last.
Put about 1 tablespoon vegetable oil or shortening in the bottom of Ebleskiver pan cup and have hot.
Pour about 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil or shortening in the bottom of each Ebleskiver pan cup which is already hot.
Pour about 2 tablespoons batter into each cup; when they are bubbling around the edge, turn ball.
You can use a fork for this; continue cooking, turning to keep from burning, until a straw comes out clean when stuck in the middle of the ball.
Serve hot with powdered sugar or jam.

title: custard pie no crust
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle top generously with nutmeg or coconut before baking at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat backpacking bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and brown sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Mix the flour and dry milk together.
Mix the 2 cups of water, salt, shortening and honey.
Now combine the yeast and flour mixtures. Add the liquids and stir well.
Put the dough into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch bread pans.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain.
Blend squash and onions. Mix with cornmeal and salt until thick.
Roll into patties.
Cover bottom of frying pan with oil.
Cook on med. high heat, turning until both sides are brown.

title: yum, yum dessert
directions: Mix butter with crushed crackers.
Spread and press crumbs in bottom of cake pan.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, combine the pudding and milk.
Mix until thick.
Cut the ice cream into mixture and continue to mix until smooth.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with dry Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: instant pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add jello.
Mix pineapple and jello until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine the cream cheese, beaten eggs, salt and sugar.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Beat well together.
Fill 36 cupcake liners with this mixture, a little more than half.
Drop one heaping teaspoon of first mixture on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift together salt, flour, cinnamon, cocoa, sugar and baking powder.
Beat butter, eggs (one at a time) and baking soda until smooth.
With a spoon stir in vanilla, grated orange peel and shredded zucchini.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: baked tomatoes with asparagus spears
directions: At low heat in a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add cheese gradually until mixture is smooth.
Add flour, stirring constantly.
Slowly add milk.
Stir until smooth once more. Sauce should be "creamy" and "pourable."
Add extra milk if necessary.
Cook at low heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Keep stirring. Drain asparagus and cut into inch pieces.
Layer asparagus and saltines alternately in a dish until all asparagus is used.
Pour cheese mixture over asparagus.
Top with more saltines.
Place casserole in hot oven to brown top saltines, 4 to 5 minutes.

title: minute pizza
directions: Put
muffins on a piece of foil.
Put sauce, pepperoni, cheese and
choice
of
toppings on each muffin.
Don't make a packet. Instead
put
foil directly on bed of coals for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Mix both ingredients together.
Put layers of Oreos in flowerpot.
Layer mixture and crumbs, ending with Oreos on top. Arrange flowers and gummy worms on top of cake; put plastic shovel on cake.

title: good chili
directions: Cook meats together well done.
Add other ingredients, while mixing constantly.
You may or may not wish to use kidney beans or you may use two cans, which is also good.
Add four full cups of water and let simmer for 2 hours with a lid on the pot.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: Cook juice, cornstarch, vinegar and egg until thick and cool. Then add cheese, marshmallows, pineapple and whipped cream.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: flour frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and then set aside to cool. Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add above ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and beat again.

title: pizza on a bun
directions: Mix all ingredients listed; spread on halves of French rolls, hard rolls, hamburg or hot dog buns.
Place under broiler until bubbly on top.
May substitute sausage, pepperoni or just cheese.

title: easy onion dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: white party crunch
directions: Melt candy coating in double boiler.
In large bowl mix all ingredients and mix until well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: maraschino coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening; add 1 cup sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: *Can use green beans instead of peas or cream of chicken soup.

title: pancakes
directions: Make batter of Biscuit Mix and water.
Brush heavy skillet with oil or butter.
Drop 1/4 cup batter at a time into skillet. Cook until bubbly with dry edges.
Flip and brown other side.

title: clams in white sauce
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Set aside.
Slowly heat oil and margarine in Dutch oven or large heavy skillet.
Saute garlic until golden (approximately 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam liquid, parsley, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Add clams.
Simmer 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: italian string beans
directions: Chop onion and garlic; saute in olive oil.
Add 3 to 4 pieces of crumbled sausage to taste.
Cook string beans 5 to 10 minutes in oil.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Season with salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook until desired tenderness.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut pickles in slices in large canning can.
Pour in salt, cover with ice and let stand 3 hours.
Drain off water and add remaining ingredients.
Heat until pickles are good and hot.
Put into ready jars.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in butter in a Dutch oven or heavy kettle over medium heat until crisp-tender.
Add tomato and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beef broth and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, juice and zucchini.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add flour mixture to beaten eggs, etc.
Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in a 10-cup Bundt pan, 35 to 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 20 to 25 minutes in 24 cupcakes.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix well; spread 1/2-inch thick in buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Cut into squares for snacks and coffee time.

title: relish
directions: Put in cans and pressure at 5 pounds for 5 minutes.

title: back to bed stew
directions: Place meat in roaster.
Sprinkle onion soup evenly on top of meat.
Pour mushroom soup over top and smooth with spoon.
Slowly pour water over top of soup.
Cover roaster and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: polo alla cacciatore(chicken)
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Heat oil in deep skillet, then brown chicken.
Add onions, green pepper, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes and wine; cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Add mushrooms and cook, covered, for 15 minutes more.
Serve.

title: hot bing cherry crepes
directions: For Filling:
Cream softened cream cheese with lemon yogurt. Add powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic buds and celery.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, water, chili powder and mushrooms. Allow to simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil. Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and Italian seasoning. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add margarine, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Center must be firm.
Cool thoroughly before serving.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: fresh fruit gazpacho soup(8 servings)
directions: Combine the tomatoes, 1 cup of the orange juice, the sugar and about half the cantaloupe cubes in a food processor.
Process until smooth.
Pour into a serving bowl.
Repeat with 1 cup orange juice.
Add to the serving bowl.
Stir.
Place the strawberries and kiwi fruit slices in the fruit puree.
Refrigerate until cold, at least 3 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle on the cardamom, just before serving.

title: blueberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Stir in pie filling and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Spoon half the gelatin mixture into a serving dish.
Chill until set. Keep remaining jello at room temperature.
Combine dairy sour cream and sugar.
Spread evenly over jello in serving dish.
Top with layer of remaining jello.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.

title: garlic fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small fillets.
Combine milk, eggs and garlic seasoning in small bowl.
Place chicken in mixture and let soak for about 30 minutes.
Roll chicken in flour and fry.
Add more garlic seasoning, salt and pepper if desired.

title: poppy seed cake with lemon glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Heat over medium heat first 3 ingredients, stirring.
When water evaporates and mixture looks like wet sand (set aside until room temperature), then add lemon juice.
Cream butter and sugar (light and fluffy).
Add lemon rind and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat after each one.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine water and butter mixtures.
Add dry ingredients, sour cream and liquid mixture.
Pour into pan (break air bubbles).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in pie shells.
Add strawberries and chill.
Add Cool Whip.

title: love and kisses chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in water.
Cool.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in small bowl until frothy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.

title: terrific new england clam chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, cook and stir bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion and continue cooking until onion is tender.
Drain clams reserving liquid.
Add clam liquid, potatoes and water to onion and bacon.
(Drain bacon grease first.) Cook until potatoes are tender; stir frequently.
About 20 minutes before serving, add clams, 2 cans of milk, salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large skillet in hot fat, brown garlic, then remove.
In same oil, saute onion until tender, then add crumbled meat; sprinkle with flour and cook, stirring, until meat loses red color.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stirring occasionally, cook over low heat to simmer, covered, for approximately 2 hours.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Stir-fry fresh vegetables and seasonings in oil for 5 minutes.
Add frozen peas. Cover and reduce heat for an additional 2 minutes until vegetables are tender but crisp.
Set aside.
Mix flour and margarine in frying pan and slowly add milk.
Stir constantly and cook until thickened (the sauce will be thin). Stir sauce into noodles and add vegetables.
Mix gently.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 4 servings.
Can add white chicken meat.

title: grandmaw georgie's pumpkin bread
directions: Cut bread slices into 4 strips.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with caraway seed and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 4 or 5 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, milk, eggs, baking powder, and salt. Then add mayonnaise.
Put small amount of oil into pan.
Then pour half of cornbread mixture into oiled pan and set aside.
Mix pepper, garlic, onion, cheese, and corn with other half of cornbread mixture, and set aside.
Brown ground chuck, and drain. Place meat on top of cornbread mixture, in oiled pan.
Then pour other half of cornbread mixture on top of meat.
Cook 45 minutes in 350 degree preheated oven.

title: green chili corn casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, over low heat, stir milk, margarine and cream cheese until melted and well blended. Stir in green chilies, garlic salt and corn. Pour into 8 X 11 1/2 inch baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is brown and bubbly. Serve hot.

title: dutch butter cookies
directions: Cream well butter; add sugar and egg; cream well.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Using a teaspoon, scoop out a spoonful, roll it then flatten.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat process until cookie sheet is full.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are golden brown.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mash up crackers and mix with sugar and melted margarine.
Pat in a 12 x 13-inch pan.
Mash until good and firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift
together flour, baking soda and salt. Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts
and
chocolate
chips
(or
plain
M&M's).
Mix thoroughly. Drop by spoonful
on
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in crumbs, coconut and chips.
Drizzle condensed milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Make jello ahead, using 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
(Use a long pan.)
Chop jello into small squares.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whip cream and then the jello.
Put in crust and refrigerate until ready to serve!

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine or butter in 8 or 9-inch baking dish while oven is preheating to 350°.
Then set aside.

title: grandma fowler's whipped angel cake
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes, milk and gelatin.
Beat egg yolks and sugar and add to milk.
Cook like a custard (not too thick).
Put to cool (not in refrigerator).
Whip the cream and add to custard mixture with vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Break into pieces any angel food cake.
Put a layer of cake, then a layer of custard.
Layer of each until all cake and custard is gone.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Great with fresh strawberries served on top of each piece.

title: berry vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients; shake to mix.
Chill before using on spinach or mixed lettuces.

title: mrs. fryer's pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine/butter in large deep pan until translucent.
Add curry, nutmeg, ginger, salt and chicken stock. Bring to boil.
Blend pumpkin, half and half and whipping cream in a blender or food processor.
Add blended mixture to onion mixture and heat slowly.
Serve steaming hot in carved-out pumpkin.
Add brandy before serving.
Garnish with sour cream and a sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: basic punch
directions: This is one of the most delicious native drinks and compares favorably with most imported teas if brewed properly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: lynette's potato soup
directions: Melt Velveeta, sour cream and cream cheese in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add potato pieces and chopped onion.
Stir to mix well.
Add bacon bits, garlic powder, salt and pepper (to taste).
Place in crock-pot.
Simmer several hours. Soup may be thinned to desired consistency with milk or half and half.
Serve with cornbread.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Wash and slice potatoes and onions approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Place potatoes, partially overlapping them, in an oiled 13 x 9-inch baking pan; top with sliced onions.

Pour melted margarine over all; sprinkle with crushed garlic, salt and pepper. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, covered; sprinkle with paprika and bake for another 20 minutes (until browned and fork-tender).

title: apricot sauce
directions: Whisk together the preserves, mustard and teriyaki sauce; serve as a dip with egg rolls or barbecued spareribs.
Makes a generous 1/2 cup.

title: hot ham and cheese quiche
directions: Serves 8.
Thaw potato patties between paper towels and press out excess water.
Lightly grease or Pam two 9-inch or
10-inch pie plates and shred potatoes, forming shells.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 375° until edges are lightly browned.
Remove shells from oven and layer cheeses and ham in them.
Scramble eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 over each pie. Continue baking at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next five ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While meat is simmering in mixing bowl, mix eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and pepper.
Cook noodles in large amount of salted boiling water until tender. Drain and rinse.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs
lightly; add the vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt. When
well	mixed,	cook
in
a
double boiler with the butter, stirring until thick like custard.	When cool, add the sweet cream.
Add a dash of pepper for a vegetable salad; omit it for apple.
This is especially good for potato salad.

title: nana's biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut 1/2 cup Crisco into flour. Add 1 cup water or milk all at once.
It might take a little more liquid.
Don't mix to mush.
Roll out and cut with round cookie cutter.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak the raisins in warm water.
Cream together the butter, brown sugar and egg. Add vanilla, oats, flour, salt, baking soda and 1/4 cup water drained from raisins.
Mix well and stir in drained raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat the egg, water and vinegar lightly.
Sift the flour and salt.
Mix shortening in flour until coarse.
Add the water mixture, a small amount at a time.
This makes a soft dough.
It will keep in the refrigerator for two weeks or longer.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water in large container. Stir until dissolved. Fold in all at once the berries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Turn half of mixture into a large bowl or casserole dish. Refrigerate until firm. Spread on layer of sour cream. Gently spoon on remainder of strawberry mixture. Refrigerate. Use 13 x 9 pan.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: india chicken curry
directions: Lightly brown onion and celery in butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add stock; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, seasonings and chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice with condiments of your choice. Serves 10.

title: summer salsa
directions: In preparation, slice green onions in thin rings.
Slice celery thin and dice.
Wash cilantro and chop leaves and stems.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with vegetables to dip.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of 10 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Press to bottom and sides.
Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease.
Spoon in meat and chunky sauce into dish.
Bake at 350° until sides of crescent rolls turn brown.
Take out and top with mozzarella cheese.

title: delicious chocolate (k-f) delight
directions: Pour the cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake. Top with the caramel topping while cake is hot.
(Punch holes in cake and pour on caramel.)
Chill cake.
Before serving, ice with the Cool Whip.
Crumble the crunched up Heath toffee bars over the Cool Whip.
Mmm!

title: baked pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (greased), combine pineapple, vanilla and sugar.
Set aside. Combine cornstarch and water until smooth.
Add beaten eggs and pineapple mixture; stir.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour.
Good with ham or holiday meals.

title: hot reuben dip
directions: Mix together and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with rye crackers or party rye bread.

title: party cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop balls into powdered sugar and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 18 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini well.
Cut off ends; do not pare.
Cook whole in boiling water for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash from shells.
Chop into small pieces, then combine with bread crumbs and rest of ingredients, except butter and 1/4 cheese.
Pile mixture into zucchini shells.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Arrange shells in large baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until brown on top.
Makes 4 servings.
This dish can be frozen ahead of time and baked as needed.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Grate eggs and cheese; add salt, mustard, mayo and black pepper.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Clean out and wash; stuff with mixture and serve.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: In 12-inch skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add chicken, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is lightly browned (7 to 9 minutes). Cook vermicelli according to package.
Add vegetables, half and half, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses to chicken mixture; reduce heat to medium.
Cook until cheese is melted (3 to 5 minutes). Add vermicelli; toss gently to coat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix milk, flour and butter.
Spread over top.
Bake in 375° oven about 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; slice the potatoes, onions and carrots to fill crock-pot 3/4 full.
Mix in hamburger, peas and tomato soup. Cook all day.

title: pumpkin patch pie(frozen)
directions: Mix sherbet in bowl until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 Cool Whip until blended.
Put into crust.
Sprinkle cookies over top.
Press into bottom layer.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours. When ready to serve, let stand 10 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine and mix first 3 ingredients. Add melted chocolate, butter, milk and vanilla to first mixture. Spread into 8 x 8-inch buttered dish.
Next, mix 1/2 cup sugar, cocoa and brown sugar.
Sprinkle this over batter as layer 2. Pour the water over as layer 3, but don't mix.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: canned beans
directions: Let the water, vinegar and sugar come to a boiling point.
Put in the beans and boil 30 minutes. Pack beans in jars and pour in boiling liquid.
Seal and put in cool dark place 30 minutes. Process for canning beans.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind
pepper with fine blade of grinder.
Mix peppers, sugar and
vinegar.
Bring
to
a brisk boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Add pectin and boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and let set 5 minutes.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Jelly may be strained.

title: brownies(4-h)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan. Double for large pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture along with cream to moisten.
Fold in apples.
