Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan in 350° oven.
Serve with sauce.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix all together and pour into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes; cool.
Spread with 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Freeze at once.

title: all in one pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients, a layer at a time.
Mix cornbread mix and pour on top.
Bake at 425° until cornbread browns.
Extra onion and peppers will improve this.
Mexican cornbread is also good.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple with lemon juice; combine with remaining ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill.

title: jet potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Top with butter and crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy mint patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine light corn syrup, softened butter or margarine and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar, about 1 cup at a time, stirring until well combined.
Stir desired food coloring into mixture.
(Or, divide mixture in half and stir a different food coloring into each portion.)
Shape candy mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place the balls 2 inches apart on a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Gently flatten each ball with the tines of a fork (or bottom glass, dipped frequently in confectioners sugar).
Let candy stand at room temperature about 3 hours or until dry.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 56 patties.

title: tomato and bacon soup
directions: Fry onion and oil in large saucepan.
Add bacon.
Add tomatoes, water, oregano, basil and ground black pepper.
Bring to boil for 10 minutes, then allow to simmer.
Add tomato paste and stock cubes, more or less according to taste.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill 7 quart jars with cucumbers.
To each jar add 1 garlic bud, 1 hot pepper and 1 slice onion.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal.
Leave for 2 weeks before opening.
Chill.

title: celery-stuffed flank steak
directions: Flatten steak and score diamond shape with knife.
In medium bowl, combine bread crumbs, celery, onion, 1 tablespoon melted butter or oleo, salt, thyme, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 2 tablespoons water.
Spread evenly on one side of steak, leaving 1-inch border. Roll steak from a long side; secure with toothpicks or string.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Fry onion in oil until brown.
Add kidney beans and water. Add salt and pepper and tomato paste.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add cut up spaghetti and simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: farmer's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar with wooden spoon as little as possible.
Add vanilla, soda, syrup and nuts and mix slightly. Put all of flour on a large board.
Gradually knead in all of flour. Divide dough and roll in long strands.
Pat down on a cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with nut mixture. Place in 350 degree oven and bake about 15 minutes.
Watch so dough doesn't get too brown.
Take out and cut diagonally.
Put back in oven to lightly brown and crisp.
Watch closely.
Don't double.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Mix ingredients by hand until hand is clean.
Chill until ready to use.
Roll dough into balls; press into small tart pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Let cool completely.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap 1/3 slice of bacon around each water chestnut. Bake in 9 x 13 inch baking dish at 350° until bacon is crisp.

title: applesauce pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Stir well; add rest of ingredients except nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle nuts on top.
Makes 3 medium pies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Set aside.
Combine cake mix, oil, sugar, vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour half of the batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over batter.
Pour the other half of the batter on top. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: texas hot dog sauce
directions: Simmer 1 hour, covered, then serve.

title: hamburger sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions. Put 1/2 hamburger in baking dish and add can of sauerkraut, then rest of hamburger. Put on dry noodles. Combine mushroom soup,
celery soup and 1/2 soup can of water. Pour over top of noodles. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cover with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 20 minutes).

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Clean all vegetables and place in large bowl.
Mix cooled pasta and vegetables together.
Top with your favorite Italian dressing, shredded Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Serves a large crowd.
Keep refrigerated.
Do not store longer than 24 hours.
It becomes soggy.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare the brownie mix and bake according to directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prick the top of the warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a fork. Drizzle the strong coffee over the top. Let the brownies cool. Crumble into pieces.
Using the pudding mix and milk, prepare according to package directions, except do not chill.

title: duck pond salad
directions: Mix thoroughly the curry, mayonnaise and juice from artichokes. Bake chicken until tender and then cut up into bite size pieces. Cook rice according to the package directions; let cool. Cut artichoke hearts into pieces. Mix ingredients together and refrigerate overnight for maximum flavor.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain, then crumble.
Mix sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs with sausage-onion mixture. Cream the cream cheese, mustard, garlic salt and pepper, then mix with sausage mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll into balls. Roll in flour.
Roll in mixture of 2 eggs and milk.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry.
Yields 60.

title: strawberry cream dessert
directions: Trim 3/4-inch from ends of ladyfingers; place ends on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Stand remaining ladyfingers around side of pan with cut sides facing in. Reserve 2 strawberries for garnish. Mash remaining strawberries. Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes, until completely dissolved. Add ice cubes; stir until melted. Add whipped topping and mashed strawberries; stir gently with wire whisk until well blended. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture is very thick and will mound. Spoon into pan. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Remove side of pan. Garnish with remaining strawberries. Makes 12 servings.

title: tandycake dessert
directions: Grease and flour a jelly roll or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs. Add sugar.
Add all but 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix well.
Add milk and butter that has been heated just to boiling.
Add vanilla.
Add baking powder which has been mixed with 2 tablespoons reserved flour.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake jelly roll for 30 minutes, 9 x 13-inch for 40 minutes.
Soften peanut butter in microwave and spread over cake.
Refrigerate until peanut butter is firm.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over cake.
Cut into bars.
Let set until firm.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a floured pan.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk.
Mix first seven ingredients together. Add soda, buttermilk and flour.
Pour eggs over batter and stir. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Thank You brand raisin pie filling, cold with lemon pudding or just plain.

title: vesta fenton's pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, mix with fork the flour, sugar and salt.
add shortening and mix until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moistened. Divide into 4 to 5 portions. Shape each into flat circle. Wrap each in waxed paper. Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Lightly flour both sides. Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Makes 4 to 5 (9-inch) crusts.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: venison or beef jerky
directions: Enough marinade for over 5 pounds meat.

title: country kitchen coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, one cup of the sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add sifted dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture with sour cream.
In a small bowl, mix nuts, brown sugar, 1/4 cup white sugar and cinnamon.
Grease tube pan.
Alternate batter, then nut mixture, ending with nut mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved. Spread atop pie, sealing to edge of pastry. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.
Cool. To prevent shrinking, carefully seal meringue to edge of pastry all the way around.

title: english toffee
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Combine butter and sugar in a small heavy saucepan and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thermometer reaches 310°.
Quickly pour into greased pan.
Cool.
Melt 1/2 of the chocolate and spread over hard candy in dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the chopped nuts.
Cool until chocolate hardens.
Turn onto waxed paper and spread remaining melted chocolate and nuts.
Break into pieces.
"Eat and get fat."

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with second crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with slightly beaten egg.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar. Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix in one bowl.
Peel enough apples for one pie (9 or 10-inch).
Pour batter mixture over the apples and mix to coat all the apples.
Pat margarine over the apples before covering with crust.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Pie is done when you put your ear to pie and hear it boiling.
Be careful!!

title: sausage skillet meal
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onion.
Drain well.
Add catsup, soup and water and heat through.
Add rice and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut with pastry blender the flour, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole in a crockpot
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Brown ground beef.
Place vegetables into crockpot, season with salt and pepper. Add beef on top, pour soup and water in together.
Cover and set on low for
6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin cookies with icing
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and pumpkin; add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: oyster-spinach casserole
directions: Coat a medium skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms, green onions and garlic; saute until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain spinach well and set aside.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
Saute rice, onion and green pepper in drippings.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: chinese egg flower soup
directions: Chop scallions medium fine.
Cut tomato into wedges.
Break the lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place about 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in wok and heat to almost smoking.
Place eggs in a cup and scramble.
Pour into oil and allow it to "flower up" before folding in to cook remaining egg.
Add soup stock, soy sauce and seasoned salt (about 1/4 teaspoon).
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, breaking up "flowers" into bite size pieces.
Add scallions, tomato and lettuce.
Bring to a boil, boiling for 1 minute, then serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fig spice cake
directions: Stew figs.
Preserved figs, well drained, may be substituted in which case add 1 teaspoonful lemon juice.
Cool, drain, then cut the figs into 1/4-inch cubes.
Measure, packing rather closely, 2 cupfuls of figs.
Combine fig juice and sour milk.
Sift before measuring sugar.
Beat butter until soft.
Add the sugar gradually. Blend these ingredients until they are very light and creamy.
Beat eggs in one at a time.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream.
Add milk and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Alternating, add dry ingredients with liquid to creamed sugar and butter.
Roll about 1-inch thick; cut and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in moderate oven, 375° to 400°, for 8 minutes.
Makes four dozen.

title: luncheon meat cups with creamed peas
directions: Melt margarine and blend in flour; add milk slowly and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add peas to sauce and heat.
Heat oil and brown luncheon meat, allowing edges to curl to form cups.
Put 2 cups together for each serving and fill with the hot creamed peas.

title: maxwell's fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from all of the canned fruit and place fruit into a bowl.
Mix in 4 big tablespoons of sour cream and 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Add sugar to your taste.
Mix well and place in refrigerator for about 3 hours or until cold.
Serve chilled in pretty glass dishes.

title: tiramisu
directions: This recipe is made in three layers, however, all ingredients will be listed in each layer section rather than all at once.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms until meat is brown.
Combine soup mix, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, Accent, lemon pepper, black pepper, Mrs. Dash and water.
Then pour over meat and cook about 10 minutes.
Drain meat and pour in the stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, creamed corn, tomato soup and Ro-Tel.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.
Add chopped cheese until melted.
Add sugar.

title: grandma roth's yummy doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Alternately add buttermilk, flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Blend until mixed.
Turn onto a floured board and knead until workable. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry and cool.
Shake in a bag with powdered sugar.

title: leftover meat in pastry case
directions: Mince roast beef; add bacon.
Combine with 1 egg, onion, rice, milk, catsup and thyme; add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.

title: lori's asparagus casserole
directions: Crumble crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Cut and place asparagus tips on top of crackers.
Pour juice evenly over asparagus and crackers.
Slice eggs and place on top of asparagus. Spread 1/2 of pimento on eggs.
Spread mushroom soup over pimento, then spread other half of pimento with juice.
Cover with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, white vinegar, water, green pepper, pimento and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and cold water; add to hot mixture.
Cook and stir until thickens and bubbles.
Cool.
Add paprika.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pork and bean sandwich
directions: On one slice of bread, layer mashed pork and beans, sprinkle with onion and layer with 1 slice of American cheese.
Cover with strip of bacon.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well. Spread broccoli in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread chicken over broccoli. Blend soup and mayonnaise. Spread
over chicken. Cover with cheese and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: winter vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add onion and garlic and cook until soft but not browned.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add broth slowly, stirring well, and return to heat.
Add all the vegetables and other ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with croutons or browned slices of French bread topped with grated cheese.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thirds lengthwise, then into 1/8-inch strips crosswise.
(If slightly frozen, it slices better.) Put into bowl. Add next 5 ingredients and marinate at least 15 minutes (longer if possible).
Stir 2 or 3 times during marinade process.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix Prego with meat in pan. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put enough lasagna noodles to cover bottom of pan, then spread a layer of ground chuck mix, then a layer of Cheddar cheese, then another layer of noodles and so on until your last or top layer will be the Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until brown and warmed through.

title: eggplant caviar(microwave 5 to 7 minutes.)
directions: Prick eggplant with fork in several places; place on paper plate or towel.
Cook on High for 6 minutes until soft.
Let cool in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Sift together in large bowl, flour, baking powder, sugar and cream of tartar.
Cut in margarine.
Mix in milk only until ingredients are blended.
Do not overmix.
Form into a ball; pat out on floured surface to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut using a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring all the ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken and noodles are cooked.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine orange juice, soy sauce and garlic powder in baking dish.
Marinate chicken breasts 4 to 5 hours.
Combine bread crumbs and sesame seed; bread both sides of chicken breasts and return to baking dish with marinade.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with marinade as sauce.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 20 minutes, then add butter and sugars; mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a hollowed out loaf of bread.
Use pieces from inside to dip in dip.

title: granny cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add pineapple with juice and eggs.
Mix and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Beat thoroughly.
Add soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Blend in. Gradually mix in flour.

title: kolache and rohliky
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
lukewarm
water
with
2 teaspoons sugar. Set
aside.
Beat
the
eggs and egg yolks in a mixer; add
1/2 cup sugar and beat again.
Add softened margarine and shortening and
mix
well.
Then add the yeast mixture, milk, lemon rind, salt and 4 cups of flour and beat well.
Put in a larger
bowl, add remaining flour a little at a time and knead in
bowl until smooth, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough may be a little
thin.
Pat top
of dough with melted margarine, cover with
towel
and
let rise in a warm place away from draft for about one hour or until doubled in size.
Punch dough down and knead again in same bowl for about 2 or 3 minutes and let rise again until doubled in size.

title: marble pound cake
directions: Bring butter, eggs and milk to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325 degree.

Grease a 9-by-5-by-3- inch loaf pan; set aside. With electric mixer, beat butter on medium speed until fluffy. Gradually add the 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each, scraping bowl often.
Add milk, lemon peel and juice, beat on low speed until blended.
Gradually add flour to beaten mixture, beating at low speed just until smooth.
Divide batter in half.
Combine chocolate, boiling water, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; Stir into half the batter.
In prepared pan, alternate spoonfuls of light and dark batters.
Using a narrow spatula, stir gently through batter to marble.
Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sift powdered sugar over cake if desired.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix well together sugar, beet juice, flour and vinegar; put in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil about 5 to 10 minutes, then add beets, salt and butter.
Bring back to boil about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into greased square casserole dish (10 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except muffin mix; blend well.
Stir in muffin mix just until moistened.
Pour into greased (I spray with Pam) 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Make layers:
cabbage, pineapple chunks, oranges, grapes, raisins and cheese.
Combine yogurt and sour cream.
Spread over salad.
Garnish with lemon/lime slices, endive and grapes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour only.
Do not over bake.

title: chili
directions: Simmer hamburger, sausage, paprika, onion and garlic 3 hours. Then add chili powder and horseradish; simmer ten minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: german kraut
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery, mustard seed and salt in pot; bring to boil. Pour over cabbage, onion and peppers; mix well. Refrigerate in container with tight fitting lid.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter; add
soups
and
water.
Mix
well.
Place rice in large pan.
Pour
soup mix over rice and mix well to moisten all rice.
Place
chicken
pieces over top of rice. Mix and sprinkle
with salt.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 225°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients with spices.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, vanilla and water.
Mix until moistened.
Blend on medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour into lightly oiled and floured Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook for 60 minutes at 350° for Bundt pan.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt
oleo
in pan, then sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Add coconut, chocolate chips and nuts; pour milk over all. Do not
stir.
Bake
for
minutes at 350° in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine water, sugar, butter, salt, grated carrots, nutmeg, cinnamon, ground cloves and raisins in a saucepan.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes. Remove from stove and cool.
Sift together flour and baking soda; add chopped walnuts.
Combine with carrot mixture.
Pour batter into 2 buttered 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pan de lote
directions: Mix together Bisquick, egg, milk, sugar, margarine and corn. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Great with chili or fried catfish.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken cacciatore(6 servings)
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour; brown in large skillet in 1/4 cup oil.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in skillet until transparent.
Add tomato sauce, water, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms; cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes, or until sauce is at desired consistency.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Use 13 x 9 baking dish. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk; stir. Pour over butter in pan. Combine sugar, peaches, lemon juice and cinnamon. Bring to a boil. Pour over batter. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: beets with horseradish sauce
directions: Combine and chill several hours, preferably overnight. Excellent as a salad or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread margarine or butter on bread slices.
Arrange 4 slices of bread in dish in one layer, overlapping slightly, if necessary. Sprinkle lightly with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Repeat, making 2 more layers.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: wheat germ corn muffins
directions: Stir together flour, wheat germ, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened; batter should be lumpy.
Grease muffin pan or line with paper bake cups; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until muffins are lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: handprint plaques
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water together until smooth.
Pour salt and warm water in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until it boils.
Pour cornstarch mixture into salt mixture and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool until you can handle it.

title: blackberry or cherry cobbler
directions: Mix batter of flour, 1 cup sugar, milk and cornstarch.
Put 3/4 cup sugar on top of first mixture (use more sugar for cherries).
Add boiling water over all, then berries or cherries. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake crunch
directions: Grease and flour pan, loaf pan or tube pan.
Sift flour before measuring.
Put back in sifter with salt and sugar and sift together.
Break eggs one at a time.
Put eggs and flavoring together and beat.
Beat Crisco and dry mixture.
Add egg mixture; add eggs and beat well.
Put in pan and cut through with spatula. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Test for doneness.
Cool.

title: idiot cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt into an 8 x 8-inch square ungreased pan.
Make an oblong hole in the center; pour in oil and vinegar.
Pour water over all.
Mix (do not beat) until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; do not overbake.

title: chocolate pecan turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk together.
Add pecan pieces; drop on buttered cookie sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler; dip chilled turtles into mixture.
Return to buttered cookie sheet until cool.
Store in tins.

title: banana molasses cupcakes
directions: Combine oil, sugar, molasses and egg, beating thoroughly until well blended.
Combine flour with soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt and add to the first mixture, alternately with mashed bananas.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into muffin tins (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 20 cupcakes. Sift powdered sugar over tops.

title: easy blueberry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes then blend with Cool Whip.
Spread half the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture and third layer of graham crackers.
Spread pie filling over the top layer.
Chill 3 hours.

title: biscuits(just like...red lobster biscuits)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk, garlic powder, and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix butter, parsley flakes, and seasoning.
Brush mixture over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: chicken & spaghetti
directions: Boil and de-bone chicken.
Saute peppers and onions in butter. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Add chicken and other ingredients to spaghetti.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk. Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Beat until fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add to crusts and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until the pie is brown on top.
Chill one hour and add your favorite topping.
Chill an additional 2 hours before serving.

title: sherry's cranberry crisp bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients with margarine until crumbly, adding oatmeal at the end so as not to totally crumble oats.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Beat cranberry sauce with a fork until it spreads easily.
Top first half of mixture with cranberry sauce.
Top cranberry sauce with remaining crumbly mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
May add nuts to top.
May use any flavor sugar-free fruit spread, orange marmalade, etc. to replace cranberry sauce.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Chop apples and nuts.
Measure and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Make a well in the center and add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir and add apples and nuts.
In a tube pan bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Mix croutons and cheese.
Put in bottom of a greased large casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over crouton-cheese layer.
Crumble 4 slices of cooked bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until eggs are set.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased Bundt pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Separate crescent rolls and lay in 12-inch deep pizza pan or a 12-inch quiche dish with dough points to the center.
Press dough together on bottom and up sides, sealing perforations.
Spoon sausage in.
Sprinkle with potatoes and top with cheese.

title: chocolate drop candies
directions: Melt butter and pour over nuts.
Add sugar, coconut, vanilla and milk.
Mix by hand and shape into small balls (no larger than a large marble).
Cool in refrigerator.
Dip balls in chocolate. Spear with toothpick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: mary's carrots
directions: Cook carrots over medium heat for 8 minutes in 1 cup water, covered, after bringing to a boil.
Place carrots in a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in all the ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until carrots are tender.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and 2/3 sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Fold in rest of ingredients (excluding egg white).
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Roll dough into small balls. Flatten with fork in 2 directions.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 15 minutes).
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: far east potato taffel
directions: Brown potatoes in a large skillet.
Stir in lamb.
Blend next 6 ingredients with 1 cup of water in small bowl.
Add to potato mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle with pimento.
Serve with peanuts, coconut, raisins and chutney. Yields 4 servings, about 455 calories each.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add shallots or scallions and cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add flour, stir to blend, and slowly add 1 c. cream, stirring constantly.
Add broth, wine and tarragon and stir over medium heat until it thickens.
Cook 5 minutes.
Beat 3 Tbsp. sauce into yolks and return yolk sauce mixture to saucepan, stirring briskly.
Cook 1 minute more and remove from heat.
Mix half of sauce with chicken and add salt to taste.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill each crepe with 3 Tbsp. of filling.
Roll and place, seam-side down, in 9 X 13 baking dish.
Thin remaining sauce with the last 1/4 c. cream and spread over crepes.
Bake 25 minutes or until sauce begins to bubble.

title: dad's favorite no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook on stovetop for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients to cooked mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill and enjoy!

title: orange delight
directions: Crumble crackers into 13 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and mix.

title: summer soup
directions: Place all the ingredients in a blender or food processor. Process until smooth.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Yields 2 or 3 servings.

title: no pastry pie
directions: Stir together berries, 1 cup sugar and 4 tablespoons flour. Set aside.

title: peach yogurt pie
directions: Combine fruit and yogurt, then fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Freeze pie until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: soft gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix together.
Form into small balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown hamburger, then place in a 3-quart baking dish. Add cut up vegetables and uncooked rice.
Add tomatoes. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss and add lite Italian dressing or dressing made of 1/2 can frozen orange juice (not mixed with water) and 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Garnish with Pepperidge Farm cheese goldfish crackers around edge of bowl.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: What I like to make best for dinner is...
Reservations.

title: scalloped cauliflower with mushroom sauce
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and cook until tender.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cut off mushroom stems and wash.
Cover with boiling water and cook until there is no liquid left.
Cut mushroom caps in small pieces and cook 5 minutes in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add onion to 3 tablespoons melted butter and cook until tender.
Add flour, milk and mushroom liquid.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, paprika and mushrooms.

title: garlic roasted potato wedges
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes in wedges (with jacket on). Boil 8 to 12 minutes in a saucepan.
Melt margarine (in a long baking dish); stir in remaining ingredients.
Add potatoes; coat with margarine mixture on both sides.
Bake 10 minutes; turn potatoes and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until lightly brown.

title: longstreth's lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add lasagna to 4 quarts of boiling water, a few sheets at a time.
Cook approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain water.
Rinse and drain.
Add margarine to prevent sticking together; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll into 1/2 cup nuts.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time; beat.
Blend in vanilla; set aside.
In a medium bowl, blend together dry ingredients.
Alternately add the flour mixture and evaporated milk to large bowl (sugar, oil, eggs).
When all other ingredients are well mixed, add poppy seed (and nuts or raisins, if any).
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or in four 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch deep loaf pans for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top of cake may be dusted with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water and let cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Freeze.
Take out one hour before serving.

title: pizza crust
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast. Gradually add hot water and oil.
Beat until well combined. Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough. Knead until smooth and elastic.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first.
Bake at 400° or until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon into deep fryer of hot grease.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking pan.
Cook at 425° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Good served with soup.

title: miracle soup
directions: This soup burns calories and fat.
Cut up first 5 ingredients into bite-sized pieces.
Cover with water and bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and onion soup and cook until desired tenderness (approximately 1 hour).

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine eggs, granulated sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, oleo and vanilla.
Whip at medium speed until thoroughly blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Continue mixing until mixture is smooth.
Spread batter evenly in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: ann's old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and milk to eggs to which pinch of salt has been added.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Mix
first four ingredients in a large pot and bring to boil. Pour
boiling
brine
into jars, packed with cucumbers, garlic and
dill.
Seal
jars
and set in a large canning pot with
hot water
and
let
boil until cucumbers change color. Take
out
of pot,
tighten jar lids and let cool.
Should be ready
to
eat in approximately 4 weeks.
This is enough brine for approximately 3 quarts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, flour, and mix well.
Beat together milk and egg yolks.
Mix all ingredients except margarine and vanilla in saucepan and stir over low heat until thickened. Add margarine and vanilla and stir until butter dissolves.
Pour into a 9 in. baked pie shell.
Top with meringue if desired.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers and vinegar in a blender.
Pour in a saucepan (remove seeds).
Combine 2 cups vinegar with green pepper in blender.
After blending, pour into saucepan with peppers.
Stir in package of Sure-Jell and sugar.
Stir and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Pour into jelly jars.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; add garlic when almost done. Remove from pan.
Rinse and drain pan.
Add vegetable oil. Stir-fry peppers 2 to 3 minutes; add snowpeas and green onion. Fry another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rice, soy sauce and water.
Cook until hot, 5 minutes on medium-low.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press a rounded tablespoon of crumb mix onto bottom of each of 6 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt in double boiler the first 6 ingredients.
Do not boil. Cream together the butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add to mix the salt, baking soda, flour and oats.
Spread 2/3 of mix in bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Cover with chocolate filling, then dot remaining mix on top.

title: herb-style green beans
directions: In 10-inch skillet, bring 1 cup water to boil.
Add green beans.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 5 minutes.
Cover and continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
In same skillet, melt butter.
Stir in beans and remaining ingredients. Cover, cook over medium heat until heated, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sole florentine(serves 2 or 3)
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until wilted.
Add spinach; stir until it becomes dark green in color.
Drain mushrooms and spinach.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place fish on counter.
Divide spinach and mushroom mixture into 4 parts.
Place one part in center of each fish piece and roll or fold over.
Place in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and pour cream over the fish.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese over and around the fish and place 1/2 tablespoon Parmesan cheese in center of each fish piece.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sunday cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp,
set aside. Place all chopped vegetables in skillet with drippings from bacon. Add sugar, vinegar, and water. Cover and cook until tender. Crumble bacon over dish and serve.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and
salt and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to mixture and enough flour for a soft dough. Knead a little.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn out on a floured board and pat out with hands.
Cut as for biscuits.
Fold in half with a pat of butter between fold.
Fold in half and pinch sides together.
Let rise until double and bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, bell pepper, celery and onion; drain fat. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole 1 hour at 350°.

title: cider stew
directions: In a large saucepan, brown the beef stew meat in the hot oil. Combine the flour, salt, pepper and dried thyme crushed into meat. Stir in the apple cider, water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add the potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Use a heavy Dutch pan.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Refrigerate.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in berries.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: soft beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix meat, teriyaki sauce and sesame seed oil into a bowl.
Mix well.
Marinate for 4 hours. Place in dehydrator for 12 to 16 hours.
Store in refrigerator in Ziploc bag.
When ready to eat, cut strips in bite size pieces, then fry on medium heat in pan just until warm.
Serve over rice or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: roll-out sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, butter, egg and vanilla together until smooth.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar. Chill.
Roll out with flour and sugar.
Mixture can also be formed into ball-like walnut shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: In food processor or blender.
Place carrots.
Blend.
Add oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and process well. Turn into well-greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour until done.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add flour and red pepper, a little at a time.
Add rice cereal.
Using a teaspoon drop the size wafers desired onto a cookie sheet; press with a fork onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zesty dressing for romaine salad or cucumbers
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the shortening and beat until the mixture is crumbly, about 2 minutes.
In a small bowl, beat the egg well; add the vinegar and water.
Pour over the flour-shortening mixture; beat until well combined, about 1 minute.
Form the dough into 4 balls; wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pizza(very good; very rich)
directions: Crust:
Combine flour and powdered sugar.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen chopped spinach, squeeze the spinach to remove excess water.
Put spinach in bowl and add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut top off the pumpernickel bread.
Remove bread from the middle and make a shell.
Cut up the bread that was removed from loaf and use it to dip into the spinach dip.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Add shortening and buttermilk. Beat 2 minutes. Add the egg whites and flavorings. Beat 2 more minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake layer pans for 25 minutes, oblong pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples and raisins together.
Mix all other ingredients together until crumbly; sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake(happy baking!)
directions: Mix dry ingredients except flour. Add eggs and oil.
Beat well. Stir in vanilla. Add flour, apples and nuts, alternating until well mixed.
Place in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Needs no frosting or icing.

title: apple cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Beat together 1/2 cup butter and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately to beaten mixture with buttermilk.
Fold in apples.

title: spot remover
directions: Great for laundry stain remover and also as a spot cleaner for carpets.
May be put into a spray bottle.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put mixture in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes. (Makes 2 pies.)

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, blend soup mix with milk.
Bring to boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese and mustard, until cheese is melted.
In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine macaroni with cheese mixture.
Top with tomato and bake 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a sprayed pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
It is good with peanuts on top or pecans and coconut inside.

title: chicken dish
directions: Grease baking dish, break up chipped beef and place on bottom of pan.
Wrap chicken breasts with bacon.
Place chicken breasts on top of chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 275 degree oven for three hours (or in a crock pot).

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each. Add potatoes.
Sift
dry
ingredients
together and add alternately with
milk.
Add
chocolate,
vanilla and fold in nuts. Pour into a 9
x 13-inch pan and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven. Top with your
favorite coconut frosting or use Cool Whip and frozen coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add grated zucchini.
Sift together 3 times the flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in chopped nuts, coconut, raisins and vanilla. Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves about 16.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, flour, oil and eggs. Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: townsend's blueberry hill muffins
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients and add milk and blueberries.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon/sugar mixture (optional). Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: yellow cake
directions: Measure sifted flour into sifter. Add sugar, baking powder and salt. Place shortening in mixing bowl. Stir just to soften. Sift in dry ingredients. Add 3/4 cup milk. Beat 2 minutes in mixer or 300 strokes by hand. Add eggs, vanilla and rest of milk. Beat 1 minute or 150 strokes by hand. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake in 375° oven in oblong pan for 30 minutes. Use powdered sugar icing.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan; line with waxed paper and grease paper.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan and set aside.
Combine cake mix and the next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; mix according to directions on box.
Spoon batter over coconut and pecans.
Combine cream cheese and butter in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often until butter melts and is smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar; spoon mixture evenly over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; flip onto plate out of pan and remove wax paper.
Ice if preferred.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the apples and sugar and let stand for 1 hour to get juicy.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dill pickle dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and small amount of pickle juice until you get the texture you like.
Dice up pickles and add to cheese and juice mixture.
Add garlic to your taste.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes, stirring several times.
Add vanilla.
Pour into bowl and chill in refrigerator.

title: camper's stew
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion. Drain off excess fat. Add pork and beans and season; mix well. Now add ketchup. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: salad oil dressing
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Lasts forever.

title: cheese onion bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk; set aside to cool.
Crumble saltine crackers and add melted margarine and curry powder.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker mixture.
Top with onions.
Add beaten eggs, salt and grated cheese to milk.
Pour milk sauce over crackers and onions.
Top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes or until set.

title: quesadillas esteban
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Heat tortillas individually in skillet (just heat, turn and remove from skillet). Spread ingredients evenly on heated tortilla.
Cover with another tortilla, making tortilla sandwich.
Stack on top of each other, cover with foil and bake at 275° to 300° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut each quesadilla into 6 wedges.

title: dilled corn and peas
directions: Place the peas, corn, red pepper and water in a saucepan; cover and cook over high heat for 2-4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender. Drain. Add butter, dill, salt if desired and pepper; toss to coat.

title: celery pecan casserole
directions: Stir milk and soup until smooth.
Add celery and pecans.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with crackers which have been mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If crumbs get brown, cover with foil.

title: marinade-flank steak
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: sissee's sweet potatoes
directions: Sliced cooked sweet
potatoes
or
yams;
peel	and cut bananas
diagonally
into	1-inch	pieces.
Divide
potatoes, bananas and pineapple on
8 squares of aluminum foil. Dot each with butter and brown
sugar to taste.
Wrap securely in foil; bake in preheated 350° oven
for
15 to 20 minutes or in electric skillet at 250°.
Top
with
marshmallows and nuts before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: glazed ham
directions: Parboil ham in pot of water for 45 minutes over medium heat. Remove rind from ham, leaving thin layer of fat.
Score fat and stud with cloves.
Place ham, fat side up, in roaster.
Blend pineapple, cider vinegar, mustard and brown sugar in blender. Pour over ham.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cover and bake for 2 hours longer or until ham is tender, basting frequently.
Uncover the last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: coke roast
directions: Put a small amount of pepper on roast and dust all sides with flour.
Brown in skillet on all sides in a small amount of oil (brown; don't cook) on medium heat.
Place in roasting pan.

title: spread-on-bread
directions: Blend ingredients, except muffins, together in large bowl. Cut English muffins in two (open up); spread your mixture onto the muffin halves.
Bake for 15 minutes, then turn on broiler (to brown) for 1 to 3 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat flour,
sugar,
vinegar and eggs and put in top of double boiler.
Add
juice from one large can chunky pineapple and
juice from
maraschino cherries.
Cook until thick (this doesn't take very
long)
and
cool.
Add
into cooked sauce, marshmallows, cut up
cherries
and cut up pineapple.
Put in large bowl
and let set in refrigerator for at least 12 hours. Then beat
whipping cream (not Dream Whip or Cool Whip).
Add this and
nuts
to custard.
Put in cupcake papers and put in muffin tins
to freeze.
Put
in covered container in freezer and they will keep a long time.
Makes about 25.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.
Mix the first 5 ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle with soup, then seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours; don't peek!

title: restuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 375°
until done (about 60 minutes).
Melt butter in a skillet.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and spoon pulp into skillet.
Mash potatoes and mix butter, using a fork. Add enough sour cream to make a moist, but not runny, mixture. Add bacon, cheese, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Scoop mixture back into potato shell.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Slice apples and place in a pie shell.
Heat apple juice and cornstarch until thickened.
Add butter, cinnamon and salt.
Pour mixture over apples.
Place the other pie crust on top of this. Crimp edges and with knife make a few slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "nannies dumplings"
directions: Beat egg and slowly add hot chicken broth to egg while stirring.
Add Crisco shortening.
Add salt, if needed.
Add all-purpose flour to suit.
Roll out and cut.
These can be used for chicken and dumplings, chicken pot pie, etc.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and cheese.
Add margarine, salt and enough milk to keep from sticking.
Cover baking dish with tin foil. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together all ingredients except mushrooms.
Bring to a boil and add mushrooms.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Refrigerate and marinate overnight.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onions until tender in 6 cups water.
Add salt, garlic salt and Accent seasoning.
Add butter, cheese and evaporated milk.
Mix flour with water.
Stir until creamy.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until well done.
Mix flour with water until dough is stiff.
Roll thin.
Cut strips and put in boiling chicken broth.
Cook until done, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream pie
directions: Blend milk and ice cream.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until blended; pour immediately
into pie shell.	Decorate with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: baked custard
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually add milk.
Pour into greased baking dish or individual custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Chunks of bread and raisins can be added to this if desired.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Brown meat; add seasoning, then soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first six ingredients with mixer.
Mix well, then add shrimp.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: First wash cucumbers and peel them.
Core out seeds and slice in round slices.
Put one cup lime in gallon of water and soak cucumbers overnight.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix well; cream until smooth.
Chill 1 hour.
Make 18 little balls about 1 inch.
Put in muffin pan and press.

title: potato salad with feta cheese
directions: Blend first 11 ingredients in blender or food processor until dressing is as smooth as possible.
Can be prepared one day in advance and refrigerated.
Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half.
Pour dressing over warm potatoes and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate up to one day in advance.
Add cheese, green onions, bell pepper, tomato, cucumber and olives to potatoes and toss gently.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken;
cut up in small pieces.
Cook noodles in broth. Remove
from heat;
add sour cream, soups and chicken. (Have a little
soupy, but not too much.) If needed, a little milk can
be added.
Pour in casserole dish.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Pour melted
margarine
over them.
Brown at 350° or 375°.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring the sugar and corn syrup just to a boil.
Add the vanilla and peanut butter; stir well.
Add the cereal and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper until cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and pie filling until thoroughly blended. Fold in the Cool Whip and marshmallows. Sprinkle nuts on top. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add mixture of flour and baking powder gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Mix together and pour over the dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before baking, take out and spread with 1 can undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Top with fresh mushrooms, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes.
May freeze before adding cheese or before adding the soup.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice and mix with ground beef.
Add onion, seasonings, parsley and egg (slightly beaten).
Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Put balls into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and soda about 5 minutes.
Add pecans. Cook until soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Drop 2 drops on waxed paper.
Let set until cool, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: walnut refrigerator cookies(diet)
directions: Cream butter with Sweet 'N Low until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy again.
Fold flour thoroughly into creamed mixture.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Shape into long roll, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least overnight.
The longer you chill, the better the cookies.

title: grandmaw hendrix tea cakes
directions: Mix together.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Roll out, cut and place on cookie sheet (greased).
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order except nuts and egg whites. Beat well.
Add nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan or bake in two loaf pans or one in a 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or a few minutes longer.
Let cool in pan before turning out on plate. Cake is moist and good!

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until thick.
Layer graham crackers, 1/2 pudding, graham crackers, 1/2 pudding and graham crackers.
Set aside.

title: sweet potatoes and topping
directions: Beat mashed, cooked sweet potatoes, sugar, softened butter, vanilla and eggs.
Place in a greased casserole or baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients together for topping.
With fingers, sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add sugar.
May add a little milk to make spreadable.
Pour into buttered pan. When ready, allow to stand at room temperature a few minutes before cutting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Crush crackers
and
set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients; shape a teaspoon
of
mixture into 1/2 to 1 inch balls. Roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet in refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
30 to 50 balls.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix together.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Will keep for 6 weeks.

title: unbaked baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Cover with aluminum foil and place over hot grill.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple pie filling in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, melted margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over pie filling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in punch bowl.
Layer half of pudding and half of pineapple.
Place half of cherry filling over all.
Be sure it is spread thicker on the edges.
Layer half of Cool Whip.
Repeat as before on second layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Then bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Heat and boil first 4 ingredients, pour hot mixture over last of the ingredients.
I use 2 cans vacuum-packed fresh like corn. After marinating salad, let set overnight in the refrigerator. Serves 12.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Blend together butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Work together until crumbly.
Pack closely over apples.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream scalloped corn
directions: Combine margarine, corn and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in sour cream. Sprinkle muffin mix over mixture and beat well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain.
Put in large bowl.
Add 1/2 bottle dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: lazy man's stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until slightly soft; then drain.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add soup, sauce, water and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in glass casserole.
Layer cabbage, then meat mixture and then kraut.
Finish with meat mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold avocado soup
directions: Combine ingredients, using only half of yogurt, in blender. Then stir in other half of yogurt.	Top with chives, if desired.

title: lillian's meatball soup
directions: *Just enough of each for flavor.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Coat chicken breasts with mustard, then dip into crumb mixture.
Place breaded chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: potato-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil potatoes, with jackets, until tender; peel and mash, adding butter, milk, grated cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Whisk until light and creamy.
Sprinkle an 8-inch buttered pie plate with breadcrumbs.
Arrange half the potato mixture in a layer and cover completely with Mozzarella slices.
Put the remaining potatoes on next, sprinkle them with breadcrumbs and dot with butter.
Bake until the top is golden brown and crusty.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans in pan (use Bundt pan).
Mix ingredients all together. Beat 4 minutes and pour in pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Open and spread crescent roll dough squares on cookie sheet. Pinch them together; bake for 10 minutes, or until brown.
Cool. Mix the cream cheese and sour cream, then spread over the top of browned crescents.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese, carrots, onions, green pepper, mushrooms, cauliflower and broccoli.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add syrup, egg and sifted dry ingredients. Chill.
Turn out on floured board and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peach pie
directions: Just slice peaches, put 1/2 c sugar on peaches and set aside. Prepare pie shell by crumbling crackers on bottom of pan and standing them up on sides of pan.
Prepare pudding mix as directed. Pour pudding into pie shell.
Dip peaches out of juice and sugar, stack on top of pudding.
Put cool whip on top of peaches garnish with a few slices of peaches.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and crushed wafers.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks butter and 1 box sugar. Spread over crust.
Chip bananas over this; spread drained pineapple over this.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts and cherries over top. Refrigerate.

title: stir-fry potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potato.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Season to taste with generous sprinklings of seasonings.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes 1 serving.

title: buttermilk, pecan chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 19 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix buttermilk with egg in shallow dish.

Mix flour, ground pecans, paprika, salt, pepper and sesame seed in another shallow dish. Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture and then in flour mixture. Place skin side down in melted margarine in baking dish, then turn to coat.
Place pecan halves around chicken and bake in moderate oven at 350° for
1 3/4 hours or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add enough milk to mix.
Roll in 1 cup finely chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: whole wheat bread ii
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german pizza
directions: In a 12-inch stove top or electric skillet over medium heat, brown beef with onion, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Remove mixture from skillet and drain fat.
Reduce heat to low. Melt butter; spread potatoes over butter and sprinkle with remaining salt.
Top with beef mixture.
Combine eggs and milk, pour over all.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; cover and heat until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes. Cut into wedges or squares to serve.
Takes 1 hour to prepare and cook.
Yields 6 servings.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Toss the cabbage, carrots and onion with the vinegar, sugar and cayenne. Add the mayonnaise and mustard. Adjust the consistency with additional mayonnaise if desired. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover and chill before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Cook in casserole dish for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken bake
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in pan.
Add cream of potato soup, water and butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package.
Stir in the juices and ginger ale.
May add cherries, fruit or liqueur of choice.
If made ahead, put the ginger ale and liqueur in when served.

title: crystallized pickles
directions: Soak pickles for 24 hours, rinse well and soak for 12 hours in clear water.
Rinse well and soak 24 hours in 1/2 pound of powdered alum and 2 gallons water.
Rinse well and soak in 2 gallons water with one small box of ginger for 6 hours.
Remove and add 3 pints of vinegar and 5 pounds of sugar; put in pickles and soak 3 hours. Put pickle spices to taste in cloth; simmer 1 hour.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hopping john
directions: Brown ground beef in bacon drippings; add beans and tomatoes. Season to taste.
Allow to simmer until desired thickness.
Serves 6.

title: mom's good chocolate cake
directions: Blend buttermilk, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to buttermilk
mixture.
Then stir in 1 cup hot water (not boiling).
Mixture will be thin.
Bake in
13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Grease and flour pan.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss raisins, carrots and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
I don't drain.
I use a little pineapple juice in the margarine dressing.

title: spinach stuffed chicken breast
directions: In medium skillet over medium high heat, melt butter or substitute.
Add onions and garlic; cook, stirring, until tender. Add spinach; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese and basil.
Loosen skin on each breast, leaving skin attached on one side.
Fill each pocket with 1/4 of the cheese mixture.
Place breasts, skin side up, in lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked. Place chicken on cutting board.
Cool slightly.
Cut each breast into 1-inch slices.
Arrange on serving platter and serve with stewed tomatoes.

title: citrus pie crust
directions: Add (blend) flour, salt, sugar, dried orange and lemon peel. Cut in with pastry cutter 1/2 cup Crisco and 2 tablespoons butter. Pour in orange juice; shape and mold.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: delicious hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni while you brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
Drain meat and season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and soup to meat; cook until soup is mixed well.
Drain macaroni and add to meat mixture.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, put 1/2 of meat mixture.
Place slices of cheese on top of this.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: custard
directions: Place
milk
in
double boiler on stove, leaving 2 cups out to mix with eggs and sugar.
Scald milk.
Beat eggs until mixed good, adding sugar gradually and mixing this well.	Add the 2 cups of cold milk to this and pour in the scalded milk. Stir and cook until thickened.
Before serving, add vanilla or lemon flavoring, whichever you like.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Place all in a bag and shake well.
Arrange in tube pan. Pour glaze over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Put sugar, flour and 1/2 of milk (3/8 cup) in margarine and stir.
Add eggs and stir well. Add rest of milk and flavoring.
Stir well.
Pour into 13 x 11-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 325° or until brown.
Let it get cold and cut into squares.

title: english pea salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together, adding peas last.
Serve on lettuce.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well before serving.
I sometimes add a can of drained fruit cocktail to this.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add bananas.

title: roth's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg whites.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Stir together and add oats. Mix well. Drop batter, a teaspoonful at a time, onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: large pan brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except only 1/2 of bits and nuts.
Put rest of bits and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna mac
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to directions on package. Then add cream of mushroom soup, tuna and dill weed.
Warm and serve.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs (1 at a time) and beat well. Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Add vanilla.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease pan.
Put broccoli on bottom.
Place uncooked chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry to make sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Heat undiluted soups in saucepan; add chilies, chicken, cheese, onion and tortilla strips.
Heat through.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top and continue cooking until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: chow mein
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pot.
Add 1 pound onions, sliced. Cook until soft.
Add 1 head of celery, cut in pieces, salt and pepper and 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Cook, covered, until celery is soft.
Add 1 can bean sprouts, drained (or Chinese mixed vegetables, drained) and 2 cups cooked meat.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Combine cold water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar. Add to meat and stir lightly.
Cook a few minutes.
Serve over rice and noodles.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, salt, pumpkin pie spice and eggs. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until done.
Mix the next 4 ingredients to make a sauce.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of potatoes and a layer of sauce until the dish is full.
Bake about 400° until the cheese melts (approximately 10 minutes).
Delightful!!

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes. Set aside to cool.
Dilute frozen orange juice and lemonade according to can directions.
Add to sugar and water. Add mashed bananas and then add pineapple juice.
Freeze until ready to use.
Thaw to slush stage.
Add ginger ale. Serves 50 to 75 people.

title: teaser pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Spoon into a 1-quart shallow serving dish. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot as a spread for crackers.
This is equally good when mixed, chilled and then shaped into a ball to be served cold.
Served warm is a most unusual appetizer.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Dust fruit and nuts with part of it.
Add extract and then fold in the flour.
Add nuts and fruits last.
Bake in loaf pans in slow oven at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: best ever corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon lightly; add onion.
Cook until tender and lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until tender (1/2 hour). Add corn.
Bring to a boil.
Add soups; bring to a boil, stirring until well blended.
Before serving, heat milk and add to the mixture.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Cook broccoli, onions, celery and pepper until tender.
Add rice and cheese.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into buttered casserole and cook at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, egg and vanilla. Add the sour milk, soda, salt, flour and rhubarb. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pear conserve
directions: Chop all ingredients, except maraschino cherries.
Blend well, cook until thick, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add cherries near end of cooking time.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: brownie sundae cake
directions: Prepare the brownie mix as directed, except spread in greased round layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Cut in wedges. Serve with ice cream and chocolate sauce.

title: stove top chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Brown rice can be used, too. After rice cooks, add other ingredients. Stir and heat on low until heated thoroughly.

title: jayne's breath of death chicken casserole
directions: Place cleaned chicken pieces in a shallow baking dish.
Blend soups, milk or cream and seasonings.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 3 to 4.
tags: cream of mushroom and cream of potato

title: salisbury steak
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs and egg. Shape into 6 patties.
Heat skillet very hot (no oil).
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, until browned.
Pour off fat.
Combine rest of soup and water and pour into skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.

title: dressing for cucumbers
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, salad dressing and onion.
Pour over cucumbers.
Serve as appetizer.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix until blended well.
Add	eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients together and add 1/4 at
a time to chocolate mixture and blend well
after each addition.	Chill
dough
for
hours.
Make 1-inch balls.
Roll in
powdered
sugar
and
space on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake	10
to 12 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 dozen.

title: grandma roblyer's meat sauce
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop peppers and onions into a 2-quart pot.
Mix all ingredients well.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low heat until rather thick.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Mix milk and brown sugar and cook until thickened.
Stir in nuts, confectioners sugar and vanilla that has been combined. Pour in pie crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan (one piece pan).
Place nuts in bottom of pan. Arrange frozen rolls in single layer over nuts.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and butterscotch pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls. Drizzle melted butter over rolls and topping. Cover and let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert on plate. Serves 10 to 12.
Excellent and easy.

title: christmas candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310° or until threads form in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon oil and coloring.
*Hold head away from mixture.* Pour in lightly greased cookie sheet; cool.
Break in pieces and coat with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Half the angel food cake and break into pieces.
Place in bottom of large, clear container. Pour half the can of pineapple and cherries over broken pieces of cake. Stir and mix instant jello pudding with 1 cup milk.
It will thicken. Spread half of jello mixture over the contents in bowl.
Put another layer of cake, pineapple, cherries and pudding mixture.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown 1 pound of meat at a time in 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet; spoon meat into a large kettle.
Saute onions in oil remaining in skillet until tender, but not browned, stirring occasionally.
Add to meat.
Then add beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar, mustard and water.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes. Serve on rolls as open-faced or closed sandwiches.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and use as sauce for outside barbecue.
