title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir together the stuffing and butter.
Add half of it, the pimentos, soup, onion and sour cream to the squash and mix together.
Butter a casserole dish.
Put half remaining stuffing mix on bottom of casserole.
Fill casserole with squash mixture. Top with remaining fourth of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared the day before.

title: apricot cream
directions: Drain the juice from the apricots.
Mash apricots through a sieve to make about 1 cup pulp.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling apricot juice.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water, salt, lemon juice and apricot pulp.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip 1 cup cream and fold lightly into thickened gelatin to give a streaked effect. Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy beef and gravy
directions: Rinse soup cans lightly with water and add to soup.
Put meat and soups together in a baking dish or pan.
Bake, covered, in oven at 325°, about 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut up the squirrel into serving size pieces.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in margarine in a deep skillet or pot.
Add 8 cups water and bring to a boil.
Add the remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 3 hours or until the meat is tender.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and seasonings with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, remaining cup of Mozzarella cheese and peppers and onion (if desired).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks. Makes 10 servings.

title: quick tartar sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, salad dressing and pickle relish in small bowl; mix well.
Yield:
16 tablespoons.

title: pickles
directions: Let vegetables stand in weak brine (1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water) to cover, overnight.
Drain.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling point.
Add vegetables and bring slowly back to boil. Remove from stove and seal in sterilized jars.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse kraut.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: blueberry yum
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cool.

title: pork chops
directions: Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan or dish.
Mix remaining 4 ingredients and spoon over chops.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook, spooning sauce onto pork chops occasionally, until done, about 30 minutes longer.
I use this sauce when I grill chops also.
Just leave enough sauce for when you turn them.
Or, use a cooking bag in the oven and leave it until they're done.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: frozen hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes and 3/4 can of crumbled onion rings.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper and pour over potatoes.
Melt margarine and pour on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle rest of onions on top.
Bake at 375° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: trailside oatmeal treats
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream together margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mix, then flour, remaining dry and liquid ingredients.
Place rounded tablespoons 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 40 + or -.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Bring sugar, cream of tartar, salt, corn syrup and water to boil.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Add to unbeaten egg white, beating constantly with mixer until frosting is of spreading consistency.
Add vanilla.
Do not use plastic bowl.

title: southern-style chili
directions: In slow cooker, combine ground beef and 6 cups of water; simmer until meat is done.
Drain fat off top.
Add onion and spices.
Simmer 30 minutes and add beans, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 1 hour and serve.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve
jellos
in boiling water.
Mix together milk, mayonnaise,
cottage cheese, salt, pineapple and nuts.
Add to jello and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken roll-ups divine
directions: Place a slice of ham and cheese on each chicken breast.
Wrap each with a slice of bacon.
Lay chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup and pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 250°.

title: linguica and pork chops and vegetables
directions: Wash pork chops and pat dry.
Place in bottom of large roasting pan.
Add peppers, onions, carrots and potatoes (rub with paprika).
Add salt, pepper, ketchup and small amount of water. Cut up linguica and place around.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until vegetables and pork chops are done.

title: easy chocolate pudding
directions: Boil water and butter or margarine.
Mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to water mixture, stirring until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken curry
directions: Heat onions and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Add curry paste (curry powder, tomato paste and water).
Brown for 2 to 3 minutes; add chicken cubes and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
If this mixture sticks, add 2 tablespoons of oil more. Season to taste.
Simmer over medium heat for another 15 minutes. At this point, add cubed potatoes or any other vegetable with 1 to 1 1/2 cups of water.
Simmer for another 30 minutes until the meat is cooked throughout and the vegetables are soft.
Serve with rice. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
To jazz it up, add raisins, nuts, and chocolate chips.
Mix well and drop dough by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet (about 2 inches apart).
Bake 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Cool and enjoy an easy scrumptious dessert.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Makes its own crust.
Mix all together.
Pour into 10-inch deep pie plate, greased.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until browned at 350°.

title: chicken sausage casserole
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery.
Brown with the sausage. Combine all other ingredients and mix with sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Crumble wafers and add sugar and melted butter.
Add nuts and orange juice.
Mix thoroughly and roll in coconut.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Saute meat and onions until meat is browned.
Drain fat.
Blend cornbread mix, corn and eggs; add milk.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with meat, chilis and then cheese. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until golden brown.

title: pork and beans(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel, reserving 2 tablespoons dripping.
Combine dripping with remaining ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Combine rhubarb with sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove cover; raise heat and cook, while stirring, until liquid evaporates and rhubarb has an applesauce consistency (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool.
Store, covered, in refrigerator until ready to serve. Makes 2 cups.

title: mock mints(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Melt bark and oil. Dip crackers in mixture; dry on wax paper.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: In a 3-quart casserole (microwave-safe), combine soup, corn, milks, green pepper, onion, salt and black pepper.
Cover; microwave at High for 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes, until hot.
Add chives and serve.
Makes 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: yummy "dinosaur" ribs
directions: Put ribs in a pot of cold water and boil.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients and marinate the ribs for at least 1 hour.
Broil.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Cover bottom of dish with Minute rice.
Put pork chops on top and add more rice on top of meat.
In a separate bowl, combine the cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and water; pour over rice and meat.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(Use the amount of rice you think your family will eat.)

title: bok choy salad
directions: In saucepan, bring vinegar, oil, sugar and soy sauce to boil. Store in refrigerator. Slice all vegetables and store in refrigerator. Melt butter in skillet with flavor packets in noodles. Break apart noodles and brown in skillet. When brown, take off heat and add almonds and sunflower seeds. Let cool. Put together when ready to serve. You can add spices (ginger, pepper to dressings).

title: pizza turnovers
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients for dough until smooth and add 2 cups flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Slightly pound chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a micro-safe dish, melt margarine and mix with oil.
Place chicken breasts in dish and coat on both sides.
Microwave at High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 1 minute.
Turn breasts over.
Microwave again at High power for 3 minutes, until chicken is done, but not overcooked.
Set aside.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and water.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together for about 5 minutes. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add sugar and hot water.
Stir. Add lemon juice and pineapple; cool.
When it begins to thicken, beat in cheese and cream, which has been whipped.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: turkey (or chicken) a la king
directions: Melt margarine and saute mushrooms and green pepper until tender on top of stove for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in mixture of flour, chicken base and milk; heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in turkey.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on pasta shells, toast or mashed potatoes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups with water and wild rice; pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 1/4 hours at 350°.
Do not peek until last half hour, then leave uncovered.

title: dirt cake
directions: Soften and cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip, confectioners sugar and oleo.
Mix vanilla pudding according to package, then mix with the cream cheese mixture.
Crush one large package Oreo cookies.
Layer in flowerpot with crushed cookies on top and bottom layer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure bran and milk into bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture. Stir only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into paper lined muffin pan (or greased muffin pan).
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms.
Beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Make a shallow well in center of each with back of spoon.
Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden at 350°.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.
Makes 12.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons lukewarm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until crumbly.
Add yeast to milk. Mix well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring slowly with a fork.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix together the first six ingredients. Then, layer a pan with tortillas, mix and cheese. Tortillas should be first, and cheese should be on top. Cover and cook 1 hour, then uncover and cook 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water with a little salt for 20 minutes.
Save broth.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well (best if done with hands).
Shape meatballs into desired size (2-inches in diameter).
Fry in saucepan, turning until browned on all sides.*
When meatballs are done and sauce has begun to cook on low, add meatballs.
Cook at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and add next 5 ingredients.
Beat and add chocolate chips and nuts or coconut.
Bake usual method at 350°.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate and sugar and let stand while mixing cake. Mix together other 5 ingredients and pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°. When cake is taken from oven, spoon lemonade mixture over the top and let stand in pan 1 hour. If icing seems too sweet, decrease or omit the sugar.

title: yummy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan and cover with 2 strips bacon, if desired.
Pour 8-ounce can tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.
Enjoy.

title: green chili cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Spray round 8 x 2-inch cake pan with nonstick cooking spray. In small bowl, combine dry ingredients; stir to mix well. In medium bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar on high speed until stiff but not dry; set aside. In another bowl, beat egg yolk with fork until frothy. Stir in warm water and vegetable oil.

Mix egg yolk mixture into dry ingredients; beat vigorously with fork for 30 seconds. Fold cornmeal mixture into egg whites. When well combined, add corn and green chili. Pour into baking pan; bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 8 servings. Cut into wedges and serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli for
5 minutes, then drain.
Mix with the other ingredients and put into a casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs mixed
with	melted	butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Pour this over chow mein noodles and form into balls on wax paper.

title: herbal lime chicken(yield: 12 servings)
directions: Combine soy sauce and egg whites; brush on chicken and place on baking sheet, skin side up.
Combine marjoram, sage, thyme and rosemary; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through.
Squeeze limes over chicken; garnish with mint.
Serve hot.
Per serving: 255 calories, 11.9 gm fat.

title: meat balls
directions: Pour water into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Roll meat into balls.
Drop into boiling water.
Let cook until water is about gone.
Add chopped onions; cook until tender.
Add tomato soup to meat balls.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Combine
ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken paprika with dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken.
Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and cut-up chicken and brown 10 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and let simmer slowly until tender.
Mix flour and sour cream, put into chicken gravy, bring to a boil and serve with dumplings.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Remove stems from tomatoes; cut in half lengthwise.
Put tomatoes in broiler pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; lightly press mixture over top of tomato halves.
Broil 6 inches from heat about 7 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred together first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
In saucepan, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over and eat.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In large pot, saut margarine and onion. Add soup, water and rice. Mix well. Add broccoli and chicken. Mix all together. Add Cheez Whiz and mix. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: honey wheat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease and flour pans.
Beat oleo and brown sugar on high speed.
Add honey.
Beat on low.
Stir in beaten eggs and flour mixture alternately.
Fold in bananas and walnuts.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chocolate chip pecan mounds
directions: In a large mixer bowl beat butter or margarine until softened. Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour and beat until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Cover and chill about 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in egg whites, then in nuts.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven about 15 minutes or until done.
(Centers will still be soft.) Remove and cool.
Makes about 60.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, mustard and mix well.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off or blot any excess grease.
Can be made day before or can be frozen.
If so, bake only 30 minutes. Cool and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish-style pot roast
directions: Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients (including all the liquid from the peas and olives).
Heat thoroughly; reduce heat and gently simmer 4 to 5 hours.

title: lemon-cabbage roll
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water.
Set aside.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until beef is light brown.
Drain.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add berries.
Add flour, soda and sugar. Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in loaf pan for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: quickie hungarian goulash
directions: Cook macaroni according to package, drain. In a large skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter; saute onions until tender. Blend in paprika, salt and garlic salt. Cut steaks into 1 inch squares and add to onion mixture, stirring occasionally to brown on all sides. Add soup (undiluted) and simmer 5 minutes. Combine sour cream with flour and cook 1-2 minutes. Combine hot macaroni with 3-4 Tbsp. of melted butter. Put goulash over macaroni. Serve immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Cook in crock-pot 6 to 8 hours.
Serve on hoagie buns; cover with gravy from roast.
Makes about 8 sandwiches.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
When mixed well, add blueberries.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake according to directions on mix box.
When cooked, make glaze using powdered sugar and juice.

title: ham and turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion
in
butter
in a skillet until tender; add flour, stirring
until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add half and half
and
sherry.
Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly, until
mixture
is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in pepper.
Add turkey,
ham,
water
chestnuts
and
mushrooms. Spoon mixture into
a
lightly greased 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle
with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons butter, mixing well.
Sprinkle evenly over other.
Bake at 350°
for
30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spiced cocoa mix
directions: Combine the milk powder, nondairy creamer, unsweetened cocoa powder, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix thoroughly.
For each serving, combine 1/3 cup cocoa mix and 3/4 cup boiling water in a mug.
Optional:
Stir 1 teaspoon coffee crystals or 1 to 2 tablespoons liqueur into each serving with a cinnamon stick.
Makes 2 3/4 cups mix (eight 6 ounce servings).

title: quick mixed vegetables
directions: Wash and slice vegetables; peel onion.
Slice and break apart. Put water and butter in large frying pan.
Layer vegetables and onion.
Salt and pepper and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cover and cook on medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. In another bowl, make pudding as directed.
Add the Cool Whip to pudding.

title: bacon, salsa topped english muffins
directions: Prepare the bacon until browned; drain.
Toast English muffins until golden brown and crisp.
Spread each muffin half with sour cream.
Break bacon slices in half; place two halves on each muffin.
Top with tomato, salsa and cheese.
Place the muffins in a baking pan.
Bake, until cheese melts, at 370°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add peanut butter and eggs.
Mix. Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into roll.
Chill again.
Cut into slices and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peppermint creams
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Add half of icing sugar to egg white.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Add few drops of oil of peppermint (too little rather than too much).
Gradually beat in more sugar until mixture is fairly stiff.

title: fried worms
directions: Buy desired number of Tootsie Rolls.
Unwrap and place in oven set at 350° for just a few minutes.
Tootsie Rolls will get pliable when warm.
Do not let them melt!
Remove and shape Tootsie Rolls into worm shape.
Dip in melted butter.
Then roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Place on aluminum foil.
Looks just like fried worms!
A delicacy!

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix sausage, onions, stuffing mix and herbs.
Roll out pastry to 18x12 inches.
Cut in half long-ways. Place a line of mixture along the middle of each piece of pastry long-ways. Brush pastry with beaten egg and fold pastry over sausage and seal.
Turn sealed side down.

Brush top with beaten egg. Slice each roll into one inch pieces and put on cookie sheet sealed side down about one inch apart. Bake at 400 for 15-20 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add beer and mix well.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. (If 2 loaf pans are used, bake 35 minutes.) Store in plastic bag. Serves 1 loaf, 16 slices.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into small balls with hands and roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together.
Pour mixture over cereal; mix well.
Pour powdered sugar over mixture in big bowl and cover bowl with lid and shake well.

title: date pudding
directions: Put dates in
a bowl and cover with boiling water.
Set aside to	cool.
Add
remaining
ingredients.
Mix and bake at 325° for 30	to 40 minutes.	When cold, break in small pieces; set aside.

title: veggie corn casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.

title: s'more cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: back home cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions. Whisk together the salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise. Set aside. Crumble half of the cooled cornbread in the bottom of a large serving dish. Layer half of all remaining ingredients. Top with half of salad dressing. Repeat layering. Garnish as desired. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: mama's corn meal dumplings, turnip greens
directions: Wash turnip greens and put in a large pan. Cook greens with meat of choice and salt. Cook about 20 minutes before adding dumplings.

title: french pie
directions: Mix
together
butter,	eggs and powdered sugar.
Layer cookie crumbs,
then
powdered
sugar
mixture, nuts, whipped cream with cherries and lastly another layer of cookie crumbs.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute
onion in margarine. Add broth, cream soups and 1 cup milk.
Heat
through.
Add	broccoli.
Heat
to bubbling. Add Cheddar cheese and let melt.

title: asian ramen noodle salad
directions: Wash and cut lettuce, broccoli and onions.
Feel free to add extra of these three to increase servings.
There will be plenty of noodle mixture and dressing.

title: 6 week bran muffins(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups bran and let stand while assembling other ingredients.

title: pie dough
directions: Make pea-sized flour and shortening by working through with hands.
Add water, a little at a time.
Do not knead, just work to a ball until mixture doesn't stick.
Roll between 2 sheets waxed paper.
Makes 2 shells.

title: peanut butter candy balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, butter and vanilla together, then roll into separate balls.
Dip in melted chocolate. Place on wax paper until dry, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: boiled shrimp in beer
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Add shrimp and return to a boil.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and allow shrimp to steam for 10 minutes.
Drain shrimp. Serve hot or cold with cocktail sauce.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread the other ingredients over butter in the exact order listed.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs 1 at a time.
Use mixer at medium speed.
Reduce mixer speed and add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Alternate with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Grease 8-inch tube pan.
Put a layer of batter in bottom of pan, then swirl around some of the cranberry sauce.
Add remaining batter and swirl the remaining cranberry sauce on top.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan after 5 minutes cooling.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by heating margarine in large skillet and blending in flour over medium heat.
Stir constantly until brown, being careful not to scorch.
Add chicken broth gradually; cook until thick and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp. Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer 10 minutes more until shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size chunks.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook 4 weeks at 465°. Will serve 3,800 people.
If more people show up, you can throw in the 2 rabbits.
Do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine sausage, salmon, crackers and onions; combine milk and eggs.
Add to salmon mixture.
Add salt and pepper; mix gently. Place in an 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese corn
directions: Mix corn and cream cheese together in slow cooker on low. Serve when cheese has melted.

title: lin's hot sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together.

title: taro chips
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over med-high heat until temp registers 375 degrees on a candy thermometer.
Slice Taro as thinly as possible using a mandolin or vegetable slicer.
Fry Taro sliced in a single layer w/o crowding them, until they are golden brown. 45 to 60 seconds per side.
Transfer chips with a slotted spoon to a paper-towel lined baking sheet.
Blot chips with paper-towels & sprinkle with salt.
Repeat with all taro serve with tropical fruit salsa.

title: velveeta macaroni
directions: Prepare noodles according to box instructions.
Put half of them in the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Cover with layer of sliced cheese.
Layer noodles and cheese until completely used. Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper; pour over top.
Cover with foil; bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: steamed cherry pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together
and add alternating with the milk.
Fold in cherries.
Bake in a greased casserole dish, setting it in a heavy, covered Dutch oven.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour. Thicken cherry juice and pour over when serving.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tasty chicken livers
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter or margarine, cook onions and green peppers 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well and roll between waxed paper.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 425° oven.
Makes one 9 inch pie crust.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter until tender. Add flour and cook about 5 minutes.
Add half and half and Cheez Whiz; let melt.
Add crawfish tails and season to taste.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Add egg noodles.

title: cheddar cheese potato bake
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and spices in large bowl.
Add potatoes and onion; toss to coat well.
In a 9 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam, spoon potato mixture in an even layer. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with basil, if desired.

title: elda's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: quick chicken, rice and broccoli
directions: Mix all but cheese and cook covered tightly at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and stir. Serves 4 with 4 grams fat per serving.

title: garlic skillet potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Add potatoes, onion and garlic powder with parsley, seasoned salt, pepper and sugar and cook, uncovered, over medium heat 25 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender and browned. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with steak, scrambled or omelets.

title: keselitsa
directions: Place oats in large bowl and crumble in yeast.
Add flour and pour in lukewarm water.
Stir all ingredients well.
Place bowl in warm place to ferment all day and night.
The following day, add 3-quarts of lukewarm water gradually and stir well.
Strain through sieve into a large pot and stir well.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly.
Add garlic and salt to taste.
If soup is thin, add a little more flour.
When the soup coats the spoon it is ready to serve.
May be served with boiled or mashed potatoes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole; sprinkle top with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs, toasted; then sprinkle 1/2 cup grated sharp cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Good to cover with foil while baking.

title: cran salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and cran fruit.
Add pecans, if desired.
Stir.
Pour into oblong Pyrex dish and refrigerate until set.
Good served with turkey, chicken or ham.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix marshmallows, sugar and Pet milk and heat.
Let mixture cool and pour over pecans, raisins, pineapple, cherries, coconut and crushed graham crackers.
Put into Pyrex dishes.
Place in the refrigerator.
Will keep long time.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Soften ice cream.
Crush Oreos in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: crock-pot barbecue beans
directions: Combine water and pork and beans.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cook on low for 6 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except sliced cheese).
Put in crock-pot that has been greased with shortening.
Put sliced cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.

title: rollo cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix flour, cocoa and baking soda into small bowl. In large bowl, beat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs. Beat well. Add flour mixture. Blend well. Shape 1 tablespoon dough around Rollo and roll into sugar. Bake for 7 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until set or slightly cracked.

title: ham salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes macaroni according to package directions on box. Drain Creamettes macaroni and rinse in cold water. Drain canned ham and cut up in small pieces.
Mix ham, salt, black pepper, onion, eggs and sweet salad cubs well together. Stir in the salad dressing and Creamettes macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together. Store in refrigerator to chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baklava
directions: Put ingredients in blender or food processor and chop.
Set aside.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dip chicken in Italian dressing until
moist. Roll in bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Line pie tin with pastry.
Fill with finely diced cooking apples.
Mix together flour, cloves, sugar and cream.
Mix well and pour over apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over all.
Bake in hot oven 10 minutes at 400° to 450°.
Reduce heat . Bake until top is brown and apples are tender.

title: orange-pecan stuffed acorn squash
directions: Halve squash; remove seeds.
Place cut side down on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until squash is tender.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shell.
Stir together pulp, sugar, butter, salt and orange peel.
Add enough orange juice (about 2 teaspoons) to make a fluffy consistency.
Refill shells; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coonhunter's cake
directions: Mix sugar with beaten eggs.
Add baking soda to flour and stir half of flour mixture into egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pineapple.
Mix well and add remaining flour and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes. Place icing on top while still warm.

title: low-fat turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook turkey in nonstick skillet over medium heat, about 10 minutes, or until turkey is no longer pink, stirring to break turkey into small pieces.
Stir in salsa.

title: egg casserole
directions: In large skillet, scramble eggs with 3/4 cup half and half. Do not add salt.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, blend chicken soup with 2/3 cup half and half.
Set aside.

title: pasta and sausage bake
directions: In skillet, brown sausage.
Drain.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, mostaccioli and Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: california horseradish and bacon dip
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble, add to California Dip.
Add the horseradish.
Chill.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Scald milk, add sugar, salt and butter.
Cool until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to milk mixture.
Add eggs and flour, beat well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 2 1/2 hours).
Stir down and pour into well-greased pan (Sally Lunn pan or tube pan).
Cover and let rise again until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake in moderate oven (400°) about 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice into thin rounds.
Cut onions into rings and separate.
In a bowl combine vinegar, sugar, salt, herbs and pepper.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate for several hours, stirring once or twice.

title: brownies(for freezer)
directions: Melt chocolate.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add melted chocolate.
Sift twice the flour, baking powder and salt.
Use a bit of the flour to mix in with chopped nut meats.
Combine all together.
Bake in 3 large cookie pans at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 105 good, big brownies.

title: ham loaves(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Grind ham and pork together; portions may vary (use less pork).
Put mustard in crumbs; beat eggs and milk together.
Add to meat mixture.
Handle as little as possible.
Shape loaves about the size of a roll.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and drain off grease.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Grind al ingredients and mix together.
Remove part of center of rolls.
Fill with mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Drain pears, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add measured liquid. Chill until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix juice half strength!

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix pound cake mix with margarine and 2 eggs.
Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 pound sugar less 1/2 cup with cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: appetizer
directions: Over low heat, melt soup, mayonnaise, milk, cream cheese and last, gelatin.
Blend in crab, water chestnuts and onions and pour in mold.
Serve with crackers or sourdough bread.

title: philly cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Add vanilla; pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° for 35 minutes or until done all the way through.
Let cool and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in small amount of water until tender. Mash and combine with grated cheese, milk, margarine, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until done; bone.
Cook broccoli. In casserole dish place broccoli and chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Toss bread crumbs.
Cook until crumbs brown.

title: mini chicken pot pies
directions: Cook peas according to the package directions; drain well. Steam the carrots in a vegetable steamer for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: quick and easy vegetable soup
directions: Place in can and heat thoroughly.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Put jello and puddings in pan.
Drain juices from pineapple and oranges; add enough water to make 3 cups.
Add juices to jello-pudding mixture and cook until thickened.
Cool.
Then mix in fruit and Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: pecan treats
directions: Spray rectangular cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Cover bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Spread chopped pecans over graham crackers.

title: red devil's ring
directions: Cream sugar and shortening or butter.
Add egg.
Mix milk and cocoa and add vinegar.
Mix flour, salt and soda and add.
Cream together.
Bake in slow oven until done.
Put in small ring pan. Add powdered sugar frosting.

title: tomato and cream cheese salad
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Heat soup to boiling and add gelatin. Pour over cheese in a bowl.
Beat with mixer.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a wet 1-quart mold.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with cottage cheese.

title: mr. attig's dilla dee-lish
directions: During night-time hours, catch armadillos by netting.
Take armadillos and wash until clean.
Remove meat from shells.
Clean shells completely and hang to drip dry.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Serve on lettuce trimmed with tomato wedges.
Chill.

title: walnut raisin quickies (cookies)
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips; melt over hot water (not boiling).
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and raisins. Mix well.
Drop by well rounded teaspoon onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in airtight container.
Heat water and add mix to taste.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions.
Mix thoroughly in a large bowl.
Let stand at least 2 hours, then drain.
Meanwhile, boil sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Cool.
Pour in cucumbers and onions.
Put this mixture in containers.
Cover and freeze.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In
a
mixing
bowl, pour water over oatmeal.
Allow to stand 10
minutes.
Add sugars and butter, stirring until the butter melts.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Sift
flour, soda, cocoa and salt together.
Add to oatmeal.
Add 1
cup
chocolate
chips,
stirring thoroughly. Pour batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan;
sprinkle remaining
cup chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Delicious!

title: never fail meringue
directions: In small saucepan, combine the 2 tablespoons of sugar and cornstarch; add water and cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Cool.
In mixer, beat egg whites, salt and vanilla.
Beat at high speed until foamy.

Gradually add 1/3 cup of sugar, beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks, then add cooled cornstarch mixture and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Place on filling, being sure to pull over edge of crust to seal. Bake at 350° until brown; check often.

title: assorted grilled hamburgers
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients and shape into 6 patties.
Broil on grill over hot coals, turning once, about 10 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix sugar with kraut and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and chill in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: santa sleigh cider
directions: Heat, stir and serve.

title: blackberry pie(see sweet dough pie crust recipe)
directions: Wash and drain berries.
(Must be drained well or pie will have too much juice.)
Combine berries, flour, sugar and spices in a bowl.
Using a sweet dough pie crust, pour berries into pie shell and dot with margarine.
Use remaining dough for top crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until brown.
Let pie cool completely before cutting.

title: fat free chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine flour, cocoa, cornstarch, powder, soda and salt.
In medium bowl using a wire whisk or fork thoroughly mix sugar and water.
Whisk in egg whites and corn syrup.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Season and cook hen in enough water to have at least 1 1/2-quarts broth.
Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Cook vermicelli in 1 1/2-quarts broth and leave it in the broth.
Add tomatoes and 1/2 the juice; add Worcestershire and cook until thick.
Cut up cheese, add to vermicelli mixture and stir until melted.
Add drained peas and the onion mixture.
Remove chicken from bone, cut into pieces and add to vermicelli mixture.
Salt and pepper well.
Place in 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy beef with peppers
directions: In medium bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons dry sherry, garlic and pepper until smooth.
Add beef.
Toss to coat well.
In small bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons sherry and water until smooth; set aside.
In wok or skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium high heat.
Add green pepper.
Stir-fry 1 minute and remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil. Add beef.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes until brown.
Add peppers. Restir cornstarch mixture and add.
Stir constantly and heat for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: polynesian paradise pudding
directions: Toss bread cubes with margarine until well coated.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake in a casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add 2 cups milk and cook slowly over low heat until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Add whipping cream, remaining 2 cups of milk, vanilla and peaches, which have been sweetened with 1 cup sugar.
Pour into 4-quart container of ice cream churn.
Freeze according to directions.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream margarine, oil, sugars, egg and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine rest of ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Place walnut size pieces of dough on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat, cook ground beef and onion until pan juices evaporate and beef is browned.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Heat mixture to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring mixture occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Tilt pan and spoon off any fat which accumulates on top of sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles as label directs; drain well in colander.

title: beet relish
directions: Grind beets, onions and green peppers.
Tie cloves in cheesecloth bag.
In large kettle, combine vegetables, clove bag, sugar, vinegar, 1/2 cup water and salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove clove bag.
Ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (half-pints) for 15 minutes. Makes 13 half-pints.

title: *seafood casserole
directions: Line a buttered baking dish with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Reserve some for the top.
Chop fine the celery, onion and olives.
Combine with tuna, crabmeat, shrimp, pepper, mayonnaise, green peppers and pimiento.
Put into crumb-lined casserole.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Pour into large bowl.
Add tuna, salt and soup.
Mix well and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with thin layer of grated cheese.

title: cheezie bread
directions: Mix mayo, cheeses and onions together. Spread on bread and broil until golden brown.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then the other ingredients. Slightly flour nuts and fruits before adding them. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, then at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: bag o' ribs
directions: In a large oven baking bag, dump flour and coat bag. Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper. With bag held firmly closed, squeeze bag to evenly mix ingredients. Place bag in Pyrex dish and ribs into bag. Tie end of bag shut, then cut 6 small slits in top. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: doritos chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; layer chicken, Doritos, cheese and corn in large casserole dish. Mix soups, milk and tomatoes. Pour over dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Tear beef into small pieces; save out enough to cover outside of cheese ball (about 1/2 cup).
Mix everything together.
Roll cheese ball into leftover chopped beef, then place other pieces into empty spots.

title: evelyn stauffer's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in water. Set aside.
To the scalded milk, add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. In a large bowl, combine milk mixture and 2 cups flour.
Mix well. Add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough that can be handled. Knead 5 minutes or so.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° until done (15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mock ice cream sandwich
directions: In a bowl, combine whipped topping and chocolate chips.
Break or cut graham crackers in half.
Spread whipped topping mixture over half of the crackers; top with remaining crackers.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze for at least 1 hour.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: wild mushroom and shallot gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine oil, shallots and garlic in small glass baking dish and cover with foil. Bake until shallots and garlic are very tender and pale golden, about 1 hour. Cool slightly. Thinly slice shallots and garlic; reserve oil in dish.

title: gold nuggets
directions: Pare, cut and cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Cool after draining.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots. Cover and let stand 12 hours.
Keeps well for some time.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Blend ingredients together. Pour into paper-lined muffin tins. Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each one. Fill 2/3 full with cheese mixture. Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with favorite topping (cherry or blueberry)!

title: angel delight salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and add to jello.
Add cream cheese and cool.
Add other ingredients except whipped cream.
Cool until congealed.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
(Cool Whip may be substituted for whipped cream.)

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining.
Beat smooth with electric mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt margarine in nonstick frying pan.
Add apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white corn salad
directions: Drain the corn and mix in a salad bowl with the tomatoes, bell pepper and onion bits.
Add the mayonnaise and salt.
Toss well. Allow to chill before serving.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: dirt cake(for kids only)
directions: Crush cookies with food processor or blender; set aside. Combine pudding and milk (mixing).
Fold in whipped topping; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Combine with pudding mixture.

title: shrimp rice curry
directions: Saute sausage meat until cooked.
Take sausage meat out of grease.
Pour off most of grease, then saute onions and celery. Add shrimp; cook until well done.
Add this to 2 cups cooked rice and add curry powder and salt, if needed.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: cream broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 3 cups of water until tender.
Remove broccoli and chop to desired size.
Add soup and cheese to water. Stir until melted.
Add broccoli and milk.
Do not boil.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Mix altogether.
If desired you may use a sugar substitute as a sweetener.

title: binghampton spiedies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: apple crisp #4
directions: Put apples in square baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, egg and salt together.
Put over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute. Remove from heat, then add vanilla, peanut butter, cocoa and oatmeal.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: hot dogs delicious
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until tender but not brown.
Stir in next 6 ingredients. Score franks; add to sauce.
Simmer until frankfurters are thoroughly heated, about 10 minutes.
Serve in hot toasted buns.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning and refried beans to desired taste.
Spread bean mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover beans with avocado dip and spread evenly.
Cover avocado dip with sour cream; spread evenly.
Cover sour cream with salsa, just enough to cover the sour cream completely.
Sprinkle salsa with olives and green chilies, if desired.
Cover completely with shredded cheese (use jalapeno Jack if desired).
Dip your favorite chip into mixture and enjoy!

title: crab dip
directions: Mix crab with the cream cheese; mix in remaining ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: In microwave-safe casserole, microwave cream cheese on Medium for 1 minute, until softened.
Add chili and top with grated cheese.
Microwave at 70% for 5 to
minutes.
Dip into it with nacho chips.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and eggs together.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cut 3 apples into small pieces and add to batter.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan about 40 minutes at 350°.
Squares should be nice and brown.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute beef, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti or use in lasagna.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in buttered baking pan.
Put sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with cheese slices.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.
When done, sprinkle top with parsley.

title: tacos
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Drain. Add corn (drained). Set aside.
Saute ground beef and onion until cooked through.
Drain. Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chili powder and hot sauce to taste.
Add to beans and corn.
In another dish, grate cheese. Chop lettuce, tomatoes, olives and onion.
In skillet, put in oil and fry tortillas quickly, will be soft.
Make filling in shell.
Enjoy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased casserole dish. Top with cooked and cut up sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Pour over casserole and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Combine soup, mushrooms and a little milk.
Pour over all and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 10.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2 pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with Fudge Frosting.

title: crockpot bbq's
directions: Place meat in crockpot.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low 3-5 hours.

title: marinated cucumber and onion salad
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together in a medium size bowl and add 3 large cucumbers (peeled and sliced) and 1 large sliced onion.
Let stand overnight to marinate.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat jello and pear juice.
Mash cream cheese and cream.
Pour jello over cheese while hot.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Serves 12.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white bean salad
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients. Stir in olive oil. In another bowl, combine balance of ingredients. Pour the lemon vinaigrette over the mixture and blend well. Chill before using. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage into strips.
Finely cut up green pepper.

title: easiest fruit cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
In large bowl, combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed milk, candied fruits and nuts.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Combine ingredients for crust and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef and egg noodles
directions: In a large roasting pan, place steak, sprinkled with meat tenderizer.
Mix liquid smoke, sausage and water.
Add to steak. Cover and place in a preheated 300° oven.
Cook for 2 hours or until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water.
Stir in cornstarch and pour over steak.
Place steak back in oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: marinated noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Rinse with cool water and drain.

title: apple ring fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add milk and egg.
Peel and core apples.
Slice into rings, about 1/4-inch.
Dip rings in batter.
Drop into skillet of 1/2-inch hot, melted shortening. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Makes 16 to 20 fritters.

title: luci's chocolate pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix sugar and cornstarch well.
In saucepan, melt chocolate squares and margarine.
Slowly add 1/2 of sugar mixture and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble Oreos; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar; set aside.
Mix together the pudding and milk and add to Cool Whip.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture.
Layer with cookie crumbs; begin and end with cookie crumbs and pudding.
May use gummy worms or flowers to decorate and serve with shovel.

title: robert redford
directions: Oil a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix flour and margarine.
Spread thinly in bottom of pan.
Brown 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, mashed with sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread in cooled pie crust.
Use pudding and cover with Cool Whip.
Put chopped nuts on top.
Any flavor of instant pudding is great.

title: german apple pie
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with vanilla and stir in 1 tablespoon of water at a time, stirring until pastry holds together.
Shape into a ball on a lightly floured surface; roll the dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Transfer to a 9-inch pie plate and trim and flute edges.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix water (110° to 115°) and yeast.
Stir to dissolve. Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Mix flour in with hands until dough is easy to handle. Turn onto lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, shape dough into rolls. Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa into a pot.
Add milk and butter; then bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in buttered pan and chill or drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: coquilles mornay
directions: In a saucepan, combine wine, 1 1/2 cups water, Tabasco and tarragon; bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and scallops; simmer, covered, until done, about 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and scallops; set aside.
Reduce liquid to 1 cup, about 15 minutes. In a separate saucepan, cook the onion in butter until translucent.
Add flour.
Slowly add milk and reduced liquid.
Add cheese, scallops and mushrooms; stir until blended.
Pour into individual ramekins; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Good with egg noodles or rice.

title: aunt martha's lemon cake with icing
directions: Fix icing first before making cake so that it can chill.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 2 ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this mixture for the topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping.
Mix well; set aside. Press remaining mixture into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange apple slices over base.
Blend sour cream and egg; spread evenly over the apple slices.
Sprinkle reserved topping mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini for 10 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon, cheese and crackers.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Add crumbled bacon, grated cheese and crushed saltines to mixture.
Toss.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine peaches, sugar and pineapple.
Boil for 15 minutes, then add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: fizzing fruit drink
directions: Pour 1/2 cup Sprite into glass.
Pour 1/2 cup favorite juice into glass and stir.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine sugar, catsup, salt and pepper; beat 5 minutes (by beater, not blender).
Add grated onion, salad oil, white vinegar, garlic salt, celery seed and paprika.
Beat 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer potatoes, onion, green pepper and cheese alternately.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour.
When mixed, add chicken broth.
Heat, stirring frequently, until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook onions (use tops as well as white part) in salad oil until soft, but not browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart baking pan with cover.
If no cover is available, use foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Toss lightly with a fork before serving.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix all ingredients together (except the pie crust).
Pour into cooled crust and refrigerate until set (3 or 4 hours).
Top with whipped topping and serve.

title: crock pot roast beef
directions: Mix all ingredients except roast.
Place roast in crock pot and pour mixture over.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Cover and microwave 18 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika or 1/2 c. shredded sharp cheese after cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: charlie browns
directions: Mix well then drop by spoonfuls on foil.

title: creamy macaroni-cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, milk and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir into macaroni; place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baby doe's beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add shredded carrot and onion.
Cook until tender. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir to melt. Blend in beer and heat.
You can garnish the top with chopped bacon bits and parsley.

title: tangy potatoes and green beans
directions: In a large skillet combine potatoes and onion; cook over medium-high heat until golden brown.
In a small bowl combine vinegar, sugar, mustard and water.
Add to skillet with green beans.
Cook over medium heat until moisture is almost gone, stirring occasionally.

title: fried fish
directions: Brown cubed dear meat.
Mix with all other ingredients in crock pot.
(Vegetables can be canned or fresh.)
Cook on high for 1 hour then turn down and cook until vegetables are done. Salt and pepper to your taste.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Put in large bowl and melt in microwave.
Add peanuts.
Cool. Drop teaspoons on wax paper.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash or cut artichokes.
Add mayonnaise, cheese, onion and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in 1 1/2-quart ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with toast rounds or crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables and let stand for 2 hours.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients for approximately 10 minutes.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Combine the apples, 3 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate batter with fruit mixture in a greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Thaw and soften bread dough.
Divide into 16 equal pieces. Roll into a rope 15 inches long.
Twist each rope into pretzel shape.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg and water.
Brush pretzels with egg mixture and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Place all ingredients except chocolate chips in large bowl and beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
It will become quite thick because of the pudding.
Fold in the chocolate chips. Bake for 50 minutes. Take from the oven. Cool for 5 minutes before turning cake out on plate.

title: weight watchers lemon delight
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender until smooth.
Pour into square pan.
Chill.
Cut into 1/4's or can put in 4 parfait containers.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving counts as 1/2 milk, 1 protein and 8 optional calories.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate, mix in pretzels and nuts, spoon on tray and refrigerate until set.
Store in airtight container.

title: fall soup(in slow cooker)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook all day until done.

title: macaroni-ham-cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Allow to drain completely.
Toss together with all ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: reunion salad
directions: In large salad bowl, arrange ingredients in layers with the lettuce on bottom and sugar on top.
Do not mix.
Store in refrigerator for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens.

title: bisquick pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes clean.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, milk, salt, pepper, eggs and cracker crumbs. Mold into loaf shape and put in baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar, water and vinegar.
Use this mixture to baste ham loaf.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in Baggies.
Have 2 bottles of ginger ale real cold.
Set Baggies out to begin to soften.
Put in bowl and pour ginger ale over.
Mix and chop.
Makes a cool slushy punch.

title: guacamole
directions: Add seasonings (to taste) to avacado. Also add onions, tomatoes, cheese, and juice. Add ingredients in very small amounts until you get the taste desired. If you need to stretch the avacado, add a LITTLE sour cream or mayonnaise.
Too much and you will not taste the avacado! Serve as a dip, on tacos, or tostadas, etc. Even good as a salad dressing.

title: spinach apple salad
directions: Mix above ingredients in large bowl.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Place Hershey bar on graham cracker and top with large marshmallow.
Microwave 30 seconds on High or until marshmallow puffs.
Remove from microwave.
Top with another graham cracker. Enjoy.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, then Pet and Eagle Brand milks.
Add enough sweet milk to fill 1-gallon freezer.
Delicious.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix rest of the ingredients.
Add to the first mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Stuff green chilies with Jack cheese.
Layer in a greased baking dish, sprinkling each layer with shredded Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
In a bowl, beat eggs until smooth; slowly add flour and mix until smooth.
Add milk and Tabasco sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chilies and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole #1
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of baking dish.
Spread cooked chicken over it. Cover with the soup.
Spread the mayonnaise and then the cheese over the soup.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Separate 6 eggs and save whites to use on top.
Place milk over heat in double boiler or in kettle over pan of water.
Heat until lukewarm.
Take out 1 pint milk to which you add eggs, sugar, salt and cornstarch, which have been mixed well.
Strain the mixture as you pour back into the remaining milk over heat. Cook until the mixture begins to thicken and a few bubbles begin to form around side of kettle.
Never boil.
Remove from heat. Flavor with nutmeg, lemon or vanilla to taste.
Beat and add 12 tablespoons sugar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in on top of custard while still warm.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a bowl.
Make a well in the center
and pour in the milk.
Stir in the milk.
Beat until fluffy and add the eggs. Beat the batter until large bubbles rise to the surface.
Let this stand, covered, and refrigerated at least 1 hour and then beat it again.
Preheat the oven to 400°. Have ready a hot ovenproof dish, about 9 x 13-inches, containing the hot beef drippings or melted butter.
Pour in the batter.
It should be about 1/2-inch high. Bake the pudding about 20 minutes. Reduce the heat to 350° and bake about 10 minutes longer.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together miracle whip, vinegar and sugar. Stir in rest of ingredients. Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: delicious chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Bone chicken and cut in cubes (breasts and thighs are best parts to use).
Mix eggs, onion and celery with chicken.
Add enough mayonnaise until it holds together.
Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with boiled eggs.

title: care a lot candy
directions: Mix butter, maple syrup and sugar.
Mix with a spoon, then with hands until soft and smooth.
Mix in granola.
Make into little balls.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: perfect blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Beat egg well; add milk.
Stir in oil and juice.
Add liquids.
Stir 20 seconds; mixture will be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: three bean skillet
directions: In a pan or electric skillet, cook oil, onion and garlic, until onion is translucent.
Discard garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese on top.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Place ham ends, peeled carrots, onion and potatoes (whole) in a pot and boil for 1 hour.
Remove ham.
Rub vegetables through a strainer.
Cut up ham and return all ingredients to stock.
Add lima beans which have been soaked in water for 12 hours.
Add celery; cook 1 hour.
Add catsup, salt and pepper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cube bacon and brown in skillet.
Do not drain.
Add flour and sugar; stir.
Add water and vinegar and cook until thick.
Pour over potatoes.
You will have to judge how much sauce needed for quantity of potatoes.
Recipe makes one cup.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 24 hours (during this time, be sure to re-mix at least 5 times).
Make into 3 rolls.
Cook on rack in oven at 50° for 8 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan (meatballs optional).
Chop onion and add to ground beef until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add all remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Add hamburger mixture. Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours.
All ingredients may be altered to personal taste.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 gallon jug.
Fill to top with water.
Shake to dissolve.
Tint, if desired, with food coloring to match color scheme.
If sherbet punch is desired, add 1 pint of favorite flavor and 1 quart of ginger ale to each 2 gallons.

title: sauerbraten stew
directions: About
hours
before
serving: In 5 quart Dutch oven, over
medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook beef for stew, 1/3 at at time, until well-browned on all sides.	With slotted spoon, remove meat to plate as it browns. In
drippings, add
more
oil
if necessary, cook onion until soft,
about 5 minutes.
Add squash, potatoes, vinegar, sugar, salt, bay
leaf and 3 cups water.
Return meat to Dutch oven. Over high heat, heat to	boiling.
Cover.
Bake	at
for 1 1/4 hours.
Stir gingersnap	crumbs	and
raisins
into stew until blended.	Stir in	frozen green beans.
Bake 15 minutes. Discard bay leaf.
Makes 8 main-dish servings.
Has about 480 calories per serving.

title: red bean pie
directions: Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie crust. Beat whites of eggs. Put on top and brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Place in greased 8-inch round baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop the onion, lettuce and tomatoes. Toss with the cheese and French dressing. Crunch the Doritos. Brown the ground meat. Add the kidney beans (drained), salt and chili powder. Add taco sauce to season.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Stir all ingredients except raisins with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously one minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Take butter knife and go around sides of loaf pan to loosen to take out of pan.

title: garlic spread
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Brown chicken and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Remove to bowl; add 2 tablespoons butter to pan.
Add flour, paste and stock.
Cook until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to pan.
Add sour cream and sherry.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Can also use turkey or beef.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar, nuts and chips. Heat oven to 350°.
Put in the cookies and turn off the oven. Leave in about 4 hours.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Put rolls in a pan; pinch together.
Spread sausage over rolls.
Add cheese; pour egg over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Thoroughly blend flour and sugar; add to eggs. Add buttermilk, melted butter and coconut.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt and spread 1/2 cup margarine in the bottom of a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over the bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook salt pork in 4-quart saucepan to render fat.
Remove cracklings and save.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Drain canned clams.
Save liquid. Add clam juice to onion along with potatoes.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
(If using fresh clams, wash well.
Steam in little water until open.
Remove from shells and chop.
Strain broth and use 2 cups to cook vegetables.)
Now add clams, cream, butter, reserved crackling and seasonings.
Heat, but don't boil.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and let boil together about 1 minute.
Add the beets, with juice and boil all together about 5 minutes or more.
These should be prepared at least one day before serving.

title: low-fat chicken fingers
directions: You will also need nonfat cooking spray.

title: pineapple walnut spread
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor. Chop and blend until smooth. Serve with date-nut bread or thin toast fingers. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Put asparagus and carrots into boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Then run under cold water.
Mix dressing, which is made up of remaining ingredients.
Pour over veggies while they are still warm.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours more, if possible.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Boil juice from pineapple.
Add boiling water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add dry jello.
Add cream cheese. Blend with electric mixer on medium.
It will be lumpy.
Add pineapple, 7-Up and nuts. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: jumbo cereal muffins
directions: Mix flours, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, milk, egg and oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix just until all flour is moistened.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Pour into 6 paper baking cup-lined (6 ounce) custard cups. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 jumbo muffins or 12 medium muffins.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together with a fork the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and butter.
Pour over apples in a buttered 9 x 12-inch dish.
Add or sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mayonnaise balls
directions: Mix all together. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, Crisco, eggs, salt and vanilla with a mixer.
Add 4 cups flour with 1 teaspoon baking powder by hand. Add buttermilk with baking soda and continue to mix by hand.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon and sugar mixture or colored sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Place on bottom rack of oven for the first 5 to 6 minutes, then move to the top rack to finish baking.

title: yum yum potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar; cool and roll again.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, and vanilla. Add flour and mix well. Form into 1 inch balls and roll into sugar. Place on ungreased sheet and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350 degrees. 10 - 12 minutes.

title: carrot puffs
directions: Grease an 8-inch square dish.
Boil carrots in salted water, uncovered; simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain carrots. Put oleo, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla in blender.
Add carrots, a few at a time, and puree.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
May be made day ahead of time and refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature before cooking.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Brown bacon and drain.
Chop cabbage; place in skillet and salt.
Crumble bacon in with cabbage.
Cook noodles in salt water. Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Add noodles to cabbage.

title: waffles - quick and easy
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
The rolls represent the linen wrappings used in covering the dead.
Dip and roll one marshmallow (representing Jesus' body) into melted butter.
The butter represents the oils used in annointing the dead body.
Roll the marshmallow in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
This mixture represents the spices used in burials.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Gradually add rest of ingredients.
Pinch size of walnut.
Put cookies on sheet; mash down slightly.
