Bake at 350° until done.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cheese and clam juice and beat until smooth.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Add clams.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole for 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
This can be prepared a day ahead.
Good served with cranberry sauce.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water, drain well.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in frying pan.
Pour stuffing mix in and brown until toasted.
Put this mixture in bottom of casserole; reserving some for top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat water until boiling point.
Mix cornstarch with sugar. Add to water and cook until clear; stir constantly.
Add dry Jell-O.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberries.
Pour in baked pie shell.
After set, cover with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour into loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can add nuts, dates or raisins (grease pan).

title: snowball salad
directions: Combine sour cream, Cool Whip and sugar with mixer; add other ingredients and freeze.
This makes a large salad and can be halved.

title: betty's homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over shortening in large bowl; stir until shortening is melted. Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast, eggs and flour to form soft dough.
Let rise, covered, in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or longer.
Knead briefly on floured surface.
Shape into rolls.
Place in greased baking dishes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
36 servings.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix together milk, sugar, flour, salt, sugar and apple pie spice. Pour over margarine (do not stir). Add cherry pie filling over the mixture.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage and Bisquick in a bowl.
Add Cheez Whiz and milk.
Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° on a cookie sheet for 10 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix thoroughly.
Add Worcestershire, garlic salt and red pepper to suit taste.
Add chopped pecans.
Shape into 2 balls; roll in chopped fresh parsley or paprika.
Refrigerate or freeze until needed.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before serving.

title: raw cranberry chutney
directions: Grind all in grinder or food processor (include apple & orange peel. Store in glass jars in refrigerator or may be frozen.

title: spicy rice mix
directions: Combine rice, bouillon and soup mix in bowl; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 cups.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix Jell-O dry with cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate for one hour and it's ready to serve.
Serves 10.

title: deluxe cheese ball
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients together; form into a large ball. Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Flatten with flat side of knife handle.
Top each with a slice of ham.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in butter.
Stir in soup and wine.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goup
directions: Fry onion in olive oil.
Remove onion and fry hamburger and sausage in oil.
Boil noodles until tender.
Drain.
Add meat, noodles and all ingredients along with the cup of grated cheese. Mix and put in casserole dish and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the bread crumbs.
Place in a 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kielbasa dip sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in double boiler to boiling point. Serve at room temperature.
This will keep in the refrigerator a long time.
Good with ham, too.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a little water (about a half cup).
Mix egg, butter and sugar.
Cut light bread into thin strips.
Crisscross bread on top of fruit.
Put egg mixture on top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: noodle beef stroganov
directions: Cut beef into strips 1 1/2
x 1/2 inch.
Melt 2 Tbsp butter in a 10 inch skillet, add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender about 8 minutes.
Remove vegetables and any liquid from skillet.
Cook and stir beef in 2 Tbsp butter until brown about 10 minutes, add water, bouillon, salt, pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer until beef is desired doneness about 15 minutes. Add vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling, stir in sour cream and mustard, heat just until hot.
Serve with hot noodles, garnish with parsley.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, rice and water together.
Dip chicken in butter and lay on top of rice and soup mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: relatively painless barbecue stuffing meat bake
directions: Take a 13 1/2 x 10 1/2 baking pan or cake pan (no stick), spray liberally with a no stick butter spray. Spread the contents of stuffing mix evenly in the baking pan, including spice packet if there is one. Take barbecue sauce, add water and mix. Roughly 1/3 water to 2/3 barbecue sauce. Pour mixture evenly on stuffing mix. Let it set and soak in a while if you have time. If you don't, it will work anyway. Take chicken legs, chicken breasts, boneless pork chops or steak, venison chops or try one of your own. Lay them on the mixture in the baking pan and coat them with barbecue sauce. Use as many as will fit or as few as you want. Use as little or as much barbecue sauce as you want. Put in a 350° preheated oven and bake for 50 to 75 minutes. If you are in a hurry, increase temperature and cut time. If you have lots of time, cut temperature to 300° to 325° and bake for 2 hours. When baked to your liking, take out and enjoy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds on top last 5 minutes of baking.

title: pizza salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients. Chill in refrigerator.
Make day or night before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix until moist and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes according to directions on box.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
according
to directions on package and drain. Combine
other ingredients and pour mixture in greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple sauce for ham
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and combine with cornstarch in a small saucepan over moderate heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add butter, sugar, spices, vinegar and green pepper.
Stir and heat 1 or 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup pineapple chunks.
Stir and cook until sauce thickens and is clear.
Serve hot over hot ham slices.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Great with avocado and mandarin oranges on a bed of lettuce.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together with spoon, spatula, etc. Chill.
Serve with cucumber slices, carrot sticks, cauliflower, broccoli or whatever you choose.
You can double or triple this recipe.

title: apple coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir muffin mix with fork to remove lumps.
Add raisins, egg and water.
Stir until moist.
Spread evenly in pan.
Lay apple slices in four rows, evenly spaced and slightly overlapping.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Blend confectioners sugar and water until smooth.
Drizzle over warm coffeecake.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Slice English muffin in half.
Let children spoon on spaghetti sauce and spread to edges.
Add grated cheese, round pepperoni sliced and olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Mix pineapple, nuts, cheese and banana. Fold in jelled jello and add Cool Whip and nuts when ready to serve.

title: western hot sauce
directions: In saucepan combine catsup, water, onion, vinegar, oil, brown sugar, Worcestershire, mustard seed, paprika, oregano, chili powder, salt, cloves, bay leaf and garlic.
Bring mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Discard bay leaf.
Use to baste hamburgers or ribs during last 10 to 15 minutes of barbecuing. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sherried beef(for crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over cooked rice and with a vegetable.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda mixture.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: raisin ham sauce
directions: Put on stove, pineapple juice, brown sugar, dry mustard, flour, water and raisins.
Bring to a boil and cook slowly to a syrup.
Pour over ham and pineapple chunks.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Cool and pour over cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate. Will keep 1 week.

title: corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl beat together eggs, milk and oil or melted shortening.
Add flour mixture and stir just until batter is smooth (do not overbeat).

title: christmas chocolate balls
directions: Mix first six ingredients and make into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips, wax and semi-sweet chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Using toothpick, dip balls into double boiler mixture and place on wax paper.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Add ingredients together; bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put on hamburger buns; top with Mozzarella cheese. Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Beat all together for 15 to 20 minutes with electric mixer until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour into tubeless torte pan, the bottom of which is lightly sprinkled with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake 55 minutes until brown crust appears.
Open oven door.
Cool torte in oven for 2 hours.
This is easy and delicious.

title: granny minor's icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers to crumbs.
Add milk, pineapple and cherries.
Mix well.
Add raisins, marshmallows, pecans and walnuts.
Mix well.
(If too dry, use a little of cherry or pineapple juice.)
Pack real tight in buttered loaf pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate for seven days.
Cut and serve.

title: zippy tuna sandwich
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine tuna, egg, pickle, celery, mayonnaise and mustard; mix gently.
Divide among 3 small airtight containers.
Chill overnight.
Store up to 3 days in the refrigerator.
For each serving, pack 1 lettuce leaf and 2 pita bread halves in separate small clear plastic bags.
Carry with 1 container of the tuna mixture in an insulated lunch box with a frozen ice pack.
To serve, place some lettuce and tuna mixture into each pita bread half.
Makes 3 servings.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Roast pecans for 30 minutes at 250°.
Melt caramels and mix into pecans.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and mix in with caramels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: coffee slush - 1
directions: Brew coffee. Melt sugar in hot coffee. Allow to cool some, then add all other ingredients. Mix together. Freeze 6-8 hours. Serve slushy.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In the morning, parboil until soft. Put in bean pot.
Add other ingredients and bake all day.
Add more boiling water from time to time, so they don't dry out.

title: baked nuts
directions: Melt the butter in a pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add the sugar slowly, beating as you go.
Add the nuts by folding them in until each nut is coated.
Spread into buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Turn every 10 minutes.
If nuts are still bubbly with butter, let them stay a little longer in oven.

title: oh so smooth pound cake
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese for 10 minutes in a mixer.
Add sugar and blend 10 minutes more.
Add flour and eggs (alternating 1 cup flour and 2 eggs) until all is added and mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend sugar and flour; add beaten egg yolks into mixture. Work with fork until all sugar is mixed and smooth.
Add beaten egg whites slowly, mixing well.
Slowly warm pineapple juice, a little at a time.
Add butter and stir.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Cool to room temperature then refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley flakes.
Add jalapeno peppers or chili sauce for variety.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Layer refried beans and salsa; top with cheese in a microwavable bowl with cover.
Microwave 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Check after 4 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in next 4 ingredients.
Chill the dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls of dough in mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
They will puff up at first, then they flatten out with crinkled tops.

title: salmon surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup and add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine fish with liquid, undiluted soup, bread crumbs, ketchup and eggs.
Spoon into 6 well-greased custard cups. Bake 35 minutes.
Unmold.
Combine 1 tablespoon milk with 2 tablespoons dry sherry and remaining soup.
Heat.
Spoon over salmon.
Garnish with parsley.

title: top of stove cookie recipe
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Let come to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon out on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: gourmet chicken and noodles
directions: When cooking chicken broth add stock of celery, a piece of onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook onions in oleo, then add broth, put noodles in and cook until done.
Add cream of mushroom soup, cream cheese, parsley, mushrooms, black olives and cooked chicken. Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with Cheddar cheese the last 15 minutes and bake uncovered.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Cook one minute after boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/3 cup peanut butter and 3 cups quick cooking oats.
Mix well.
Spoon out on greased cookie sheet.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom sauce
directions: Mix meat, salt and pepper and shape into 4 patties.
Pan-fry in lightly greased skillet until desired doneness.
Remove from skillet and keep hot.
Cook mushrooms in butter or margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in flour and curry powder.
Add water and bouillon cube; cook until smooth and thickened.
Pour over meat patties and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southern fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal,
salt and pepper in a small bowl; stir well. Dip tomato slices in beaten egg; dredge in cornmeal mixture, coating well on both sides.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add one layer of tomato slices and fry 3 to 5 minutes or until browned, turning once. Remove slices from skillet.
Drain; set aside and keep warm. Repeat procedure.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: rocky road(a holiday favorite the kids can do!)
directions: Mix very soft margarine and graham cracker crumbs into 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Layer rest of ingredients with the condensed milk last.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 1/2 way and cut into squares.
Better make 2 batches!

title: julie's chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in pie shell.
Cover with other pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "ghetti"
directions: Go in the kitchen.
Ask daddy to cook.
Eat.
Have with bread and salad.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery until tender and drain.
Mix water chestnuts with soup and 1/2 of butter (melted).
Put in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and toss with remaining butter.
Put on top of the celery mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pork and pasta bake
directions: Prepare ziti as label directs; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook pork sausage until well browned, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in Ricotta, next 3 ingredients and half sauce.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over ziti mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: best brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up into bite size pieces.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese and onions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.
Add onion rings and bake 3 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: featherbed rolls
directions: Cook potato in boiling water until done.
Drain and reserve 3/4 cup liquid.
Mash potato.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
In large bowl combine potato water, sugar, butter and salt.
Let stand until butter is melted and mixture is warm.
Add yeast.
Let stand until softened.
Beat in egg and potato.
Stir in as much flour as you can.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes to make medium soft dough.
Put in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 3 inch cutter. Place 1/4 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until brown.
Makes 16.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Stir together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk.
Cook to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Serve warm over cake.

title: smothered tomatoes and okra
directions: Wash
okra;
cut
and
fry
in
tablespoons oil.
In separate skillet make a medium dark roux with 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add
chopped
onion,
bell pepper and celery; let simmer until wilted.
Add
tomatoes
and simmer 5 minutes. Add okra and season
to
taste with salt and pepper. Turn to medium heat and cook
for
30 minutes. Then let simmer for 15 minutes on low heat to let flavors blend together.

title: spaghetti sauce with noodles(feeds 30 people)
directions: Saute beef with onions and celery; drain and discard fat.
Put all ingredients in a large heavy pot and simmer several hours. Serve over 5 pounds of spaghetti, cooked.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Beat butter or margarine; add sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour and salt and add to the butter mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Dough will be stiff.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (makes 25 to 30).
Place close together on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes. (Do not brown.)
Allow to cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: not your ordinary fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve.
You can add any fresh fruit or leave out any fruit to customize this salad to your own taste.
You can also use frozen or canned fruit when not in season - but fresh is best.
This is a very colorful and festive salad.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine whole wheat flour and yeast. Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly, to melt shortening.
Add to dry mixture; add eggs.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough all-purpose flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Turn out on floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once. Cover and let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down. Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 24 rolls.
Place on greased baking sheets. Cover and let rise until almost double (about 45 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: yangnyum kanjang - bulgogi sauce
directions: Put soy sauce and sesame oil in a small bowl and stir in next 6 ingredients.
Crush garlic with salt and sugar to a fine paste. Stir in.
Mix well and serve in small individual sauce dishes.

title: orange pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with mandarin oranges and instant pudding until blended.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Spoon into 9-inch square dish.
Top with crushed nuts and refrigerate for an hour or more.

title: cherry cheese cake brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add flour to brownie mix; otherwise, prepare as directed, except bake for 25 minutes.
Beat vanilla, egg, milk and cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Pour over brownies.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until top sets.
Cool. Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Serve.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix together sugar and flour. Blend eggs into mixture. Melt oleo and chocolate. Use whisk, not beater. Add chocolate and oleo to first 3 ingredients. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Use foil cup liners on cookie sheet and spray with Pam. Fill 1/2 full. Makes 22 to 24. Bake at 325° for 22 minutes (cracks on top like brownies). Don't overbake.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crispy.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve bacon grease in skillet.
Add onion.
Cook on medium heat until tender.
Add sugar, a dash of pepper and stir together.
Add vinegar and mix.
Add cabbage and cook until tender.
Put into a casserole dish and crumble bacon over the top. Serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions in 2 tablespoons oil, stirring constantly until fine.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: mom ever's shortcake
directions: Beat butter together with eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Spread in 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° (may need longer).
Recipe may be doubled for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Great with strawberries and milk!

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. In another bowl, mix all wet ingredients together. Fold dry ingredients into wet ingredients, stirring until well mixed. Do not overmix. (Add chocolate chips, if desired.)
Fill foil-lined muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Makes 24 muffins.

title: mary stratton smith's jello cake
directions: Mix cake and Jell-O.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add Wesson oil, milk and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk; mix well and let set until thickens. Add cream cheese and Cool Whip. Layer cookies, bananas and pudding, ending up with pudding on top. May crumble up wafers on top. Chill for approximately 4 hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter or oleo in a saucepan.
Combine with candy bars.
Place over low heat until candy bars are melted, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour in oblong cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350°.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cornflake crumbs, Parmesan cheese and dash of pepper.
Dip veal in egg and then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 minutes longer, or until tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place dry ingredients into bowl; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Place pecan halves (4) on top of small loaf pan.
Makes 5 small loaves.
Bake at 325° for approximately 50 minutes or until baked.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Place in large bowl; add cold water to cover.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with cooking spray.
Set aside.
Dry potatoes with paper towels. Transfer potatoes to a clean large towel.
Sprinkle with oil, pepper and salt; toss gently to combine, then arrange on prepared cooking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Turn potatoes and sprinkle with garlic.
Bake until golden.
Turn as needed for even browning.
Serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cover bottom of serving bowl with graham crackers.
Mix instant pudding and milk on low speed 2 minutes, then whisk in the sour cream.
Put half of the banana slices on the graham crackers, then cover with half of the pudding mixture.
Cover pudding with graham crackers.
Top with remaining bananas, then remaining pudding.
Spread with Cool Whip and chill 3 hours.

title: gram alice's lemon dreams
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar, cup of flour and salt. Line 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Don't brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Microwave butter, onions and bell pepper for 5 to 6 minutes. Mix eggs, corn and muffin mix. Combine all ingredients except cheese and pour into greased baking dish, Pam is recommended. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: doug cooper's apricot cashew glazed turkey
directions: Heat a small pan over moderate heat and saute cashews in oil for approximately 1 minute, then add in apricots and cook for 1 minute.
Pour in orange juice and Zinfindel.
Reduce to half. Finish by adding syrup and jelly.
Let cook until it thickens. Lightly season turkey slices and grill for approximately 4 minutes on each side.
Slice turkey on an angle and serve over glaze. Serve with yam slices.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients by hand and press down into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Combine both mixtures.
Chill for one hour. Roll into balls, roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: holiday munchies
directions: Mix well and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole(crock-pot meal)
directions: Lightly grease crock-pot or spray with cooking spray. Place chicken breasts in pot. Top with cheese. Combine soup and milk, stirring well. Spoon over cheese; sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle melted butter over stuffing mix. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours. Serves 6.

title: beet molded salad
directions: Drain beets and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Heat to boiling and add to gelatin, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm. Good topped with sour cream, mayonnaise or yogurt.

title: hummingbird cake(for my husband)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Make a well in mixture and add Wesson oil and beaten eggs.
Stir by hand; batter will be stiff.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into small Dixie cups.
Let dry overnight.
Peel away paper.

title: tater tot special
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Place meat in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Place onion over meat.
Mix soups together and pour over meat and onion.
Place frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Simmer the first four ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients except sour cream and chives and cook until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.
Add sour cream and chives just before serving.

title: chewies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs into mixture, then stir in flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well.
Let stand for 5 minutes so oats will absorb moisture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes on cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spam and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare your macaroni and cheese.
In a small saucepan, melt your extra cheese and margarine, then add milk.
Stir until smooth. In another saucepan, fix your soup as directed.
Add your onion and pepper.
Cook until about half done, then mix all ingredients together well.
Put in large casserole dish and bake in oven at 300° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: three-loaf pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add sugar, oil, eggs and coffee; mix. Then, add pumpkin and pudding mix, then nuts.
Grease pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool on rack.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together baking soda, cinnamon and pumpkin.
Mix in eggs, sugar and flour. Grease cookie sheet with edges all around.
Line with waxed paper. Pour cake mixture onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and flip onto a clean tea towel.
Peel off waxed paper.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar. Roll like a log and refrigerate to cool 15 minutes to 1/2 hour.

title: cheese ham squares
directions: Cut bread on diagonal and place 1/2 of it buttered side down in greased dish.
Mix ham and mustard and spread on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with remaining bread.
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning and pour over bread.
Chill several hours or overnight. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: grandma arbuckle's doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients; let rise for 45 minutes.
Roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut and let rise for at least 30 minutes.
Fry in deep fat until they float to the top.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Measure sugar, water and peel into saucepan.
Stir constantly, bringing to a boil, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool. Squeeze lemon juice and add it to cooled sugar mixture (this is now the lemonade syrup).
Pour syrup into container and cover tightly.
Can be kept in fridge 2 to 3 weeks.
When ready to serve, put 2 to 3 ice cubes in glass.
Pour 1/4 cup of syrup over cubes and add 3/4 cup cold water.
Stir.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Fill tortillas and place in baking dish (spray dish with Pam).
Pour remaining mixture over tortillas.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oats; let stand 20 minutes. Mix the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in the oats and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whip cream pound cake
directions: Cream
together
butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing
well after each egg.
Add alternately flour and whipping cream.
Add
flavorings.
Put in ungreased tube pan. Start in cold
oven at 325° and bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in large casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and the 1/2 jar cherries.
Bake 2 hours at 275° in preheated oven.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil the margarine, sugar and Karo syrup together.
Add vanilla.
Pop the popcorn.
Pour sugar mixture over the popcorn. Place in pan and bake in oven at 200° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: venison burgers
directions: The toughest part of the deer can be used for venison burger. Grind the meat with a meat grinder.
Mix in salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped onion, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. All these ingredients are to individual taste and it is nearly impossible to add too much of any ingredient, except salt of course.
Make the mixture into patties and fry or grill until well done.

title: chicken strata
directions: Cut two slices of bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place in bottom of 8 x 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, chopped vegetables, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spread on bread cubes.
Cut 2 more slices of bread into 1-inch cubes and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill one hour or overnight.
Sprinkle soup over top and cover with two buttered slices of bread cut into 1-inch cubes.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top, bake another 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Pour in well-greased, floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle a clean towel with powdered sugar.
Flip hot cake out on towel.
Roll up towel in jelly roll fashion and let cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together ice cream, Cool Whip and lemonade.
Add food color.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm, about 2 to 3 hours.
This is a refreshing summertime dessert.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tracy and greg's best blonde brownies
directions: Combine sugars and butter in medium boiler.
Stir on low heat until butter is melted.
Cool.
Add eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate drops over top.
Bake about 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Do not overbake.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix or use medium speed on electric mixer the flour, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Grease and flour a square pan.
Pour batter in the bottom of pan.
Top with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with a small amount of flour and sugar/cinnamon
mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Saute onion, celery and pepper.
Add potatoes, carrots, salmon liquid, broth and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Add peas and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add salmon, corn and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cut roast into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge meat and brown in oil in frying pan.
Remove meat from pan; add the remaining flour mixture to drippings.
Blend until smooth.
Return meat to frying pan; cover with onions.
Pour the remaining ingredients over meat and onions.
Cover; simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Great with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Combine cheeses and egg in small bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly on bread, covering to edge. Lay a piece of asparagus on each slice of bread.
Roll up tightly; secure with 3 toothpicks.
Dip in melted butter.
Put on baking sheet.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw slightly.
Slice in 3 equal pieces.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 60 pieces.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Cook over low flame for about 5 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper until cool.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding decreasing milk by 1/2 cup per package.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Layer with graham crackers.
Cover with frosting.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: autumn cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add lemon juice, cranberry sauce, celery, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serves 25.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage until tender, but crisp; drain.
Mix shallot, garlic, bread crumbs and cheese.
In baking pan, layer cabbage, tomatoes and then bread crumb mixture.
Repeat to make one more layer.
Drizzle olive oil over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, coca, cream and butter in a pan for 1 1/2 minutes, boiling hard and stirring constantly on high heat.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats and drop quickly by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Break up ground beef and put in pan with sliced onions and minced garlic glove.
Brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and water/wine.
Bring to boil.
Add seasonings and noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: zuchinia salad
directions: Wash zuchinia; cut into small pieces.
Place the pan onto stove.
Put the zuchinia into the pan.
Add salt and two cups of water.
Leave on stove until water boils and the zuchinia gets soft.
Then beat the garlic.
Mix garlic and yogurt together and the zuchinia, place into plate, then add parsley on top.

title: cheese and mushroom manicotti
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of the Mozzarella with Cheddar cheese, mushrooms, olives, onion, celery, crumbs, egg, milk, parsley and pepper; set aside.

title: trash
directions: You will need 1 white, unscented garbage bag.
